<TITLE>SIA Conferences & Meetings</TITLE>
<body background="sia3abac.gif"><IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><B><I>Conferences & Meetings</I></B></FONT><BR><BR>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=3> <FONT SIZE=3>Program information on SIA conferences, along with registration forms, is sent automatically to appropriate individuals within SIA's membership, including those who attended the prior year.  Questions regarding conferences may be directed to <A HREF=mailto:mbattista@sia.com>Mary Ann Battista</A>, <A HREF=mailto:dserri@sia.com>Diana Serri</A> or <A HREF=mailto:mgaul@sia.com>Melanie Gaul.</A>  For sponsorship and exhibit information, contact <A HREF=mailto:dfitzell@sia.com>Doris Fitzell.</A></FONT><BR><BR>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
<TABLE WIDTH=100%><FONT SIZE=4>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <A HREF="#annual"><STRONG>Annual Meeting</STRONG></A></TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <A HREF="#legal"><STRONG>Compliance & Legal Seminar</STRONG></A></TD></TR>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <A HREF="#fmd"><STRONG>Financial Management Division<BR> <dd>Regional Conference</STRONG></A></TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <A HREF="#info"><STRONG>Information Management Conference <BR><dd>& Exhibit</STRONG></A></TD></TR>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG><A HREF="#net"><STRONG>Internet Update Conference</STRONG></A></TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG><A HREF="#local"><STRONG>Local Firms Conference</STRONG></A> </TD></TR>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"><A HREF="#ops"><STRONG>Operations Conference & Exhibit</STRONG></A></TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <A HREF="#update"><STRONG>Operations Update Conference</STRONG></A></TD></TR>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"><A HREF="#reg"><STRONG>Regional Firms Conference</STRONG></A></TD>
<TD> <IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <A HREF="#ira"><STRONG>Retirement Conference</STRONG></A></TD></TR>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"><A HREF="#sales"><STRONG>Retail Management Conference (Formerly<BR><dd> Sales and Marketing)</STRONG></A></TD>
<FONT></TABLE>
<P>
<A NAME="annual"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Annual Meeting -- SIA Members Only</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>The SIA Annual Meeting was held from November 6-9, 1996 at the Boca Raton Resort & Club in Boca Raton, Fl.  It is the major membership meeting of the year, and this year's program included general session addresses by industry and government leaders, as well as meetings of committees, districts and the board of SIA.  In addition, the Annual Meeting provides a premier opportunity for managers of all functional areas to meet and discuss business with their counterparts from across the country.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:mgaul@sia.com>Melanie Gaul</A>.</FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="legal"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Compliance and Legal Seminar</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>The 1997 seminar will be held March 16-19 at the Grand Cypress in Orlando, FL.  This seminar attracts legal and compliance professionals from securities firms across the country. Discussions center on a range of legal and regulatory developments in the securities industry.  Sponsored by SIA's Compliance and Legal Division.  Contact Dan Goldstein, Compliance and Legal Division, (518) 785-0721.</FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="fmd"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Financial Management Division Regional Conference</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>The fourth annual regional conference is sponsored by SIA's Financial Management Division and will be held June 16-17, 1997, at the Omni Chicago Hotel.  The program included general sessions and concurrent workshops fielding speakers from the securities industry, accounting firms, regulators, SROs, and leading industry vendors targeting an audience of accounting, tax, regulatory and financial professionals in the securities industry. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:gmonahan@sia.com>George Monahan</A></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="info"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Information Management Conference & Exhibit</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>This conference was held June 4-6, 1996 at the New York Hilton.  It included an extensive exhibit of communications and computer products and services. The program featured addresses, panels and workshops designed for those involved with or responsible for technology activities at SIA member  firms, including communications, data processing and market data.  The theme was "The Business of Technology".  Next year's conference is scheduled for June 24-26, 1997 at the New York Hilton.   Sponsored by SIA's <A HREF="sia01d.htm#TIM">Technology Management Committee</A>.  For conference information contact: <A HREF=mailto:pgoodbody@sia.com>Pim Goodbody.</A>  For sponsorship and exhibit information, contact <A HREF=mailto:dfitzell@sia.com>Doris Fitzell.</A></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="net"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Internet Update Conference</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>On February 3, 1997 an Internet update conference will be held at the Marriott Marquis New York.  This is a one-day conference for securities industry professionals who want to know more about Internet technology and how it is affecting their business.  Participants will be brought up-to-date on what is going on in the regulatory arena to facilitate the use of the Internet and related new technologies, as well as on how securities firms are using them.  For your information and use, the <A HREF="int-up.htm">conference program</A>, <A HREF="int-reg.htm">registration form</A>, and <A HREF="int-form.htm">hotel & travel information</A> is available.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:pcassar@sia.com>Phyllis Cassar</A>.</FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="local"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Local Firms Conference & Exhibit</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>The 8th annual conference was held October 10-12, 1996 at the Hyatt Regency Hotel in Cincinnati, OH.  The conference dealt specifically with topics of concern to smaller SIA member firms.   Next year's conference is scheduled for October 15-17, 1997 at the Wyndham Greenspoint Hotel in Houston, TX.  The Conference is sponsored by SIA's <A HREF="sia01d.htm#LF">Local Firms Committee</A>.  Contact : <A HREF=mailto:rgannon@sia.com>Rob Gannon</A></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="ops"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Operations Conference & Exhibit</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>The 1997 Annual Operations Conference and Exhibit will be held April 30-May 3, 1997.   It will be held at the Marriott's Orlando World Center in Orlando, FL.  The conference provides operations professionals with ideas and solutions for achieving the highest quality of performance and customer service within their functional area of responsibility.    Sponsored by SIA's <A HREF="sia01d.htm#OPS">Operations Committee</A>.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:tmonahan@sia.com>Tom Monahan</A></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="update"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Operations Update Conference</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>This year's conference was held on November 21, 1996 at the New York Hilton Hotel in New York City.   This program has become an important follow-up to SIA's Spring Operations Conference.  Sponsored by SIA's <A HREF="sia01d.htm#OPS">Operations Committee</A>.  Contact: <A  HREF=mailto:tmonahan@sia.com>Tom Monahan</A></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="reg"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Regional Firms Conference</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>The 1997 edition of this annual management meeting will be held May 6-7, 1997 at the Fairmont Hotel in Chicago, IL.   As in the past, the program will center on matters of principal interest to executives in mid-size firms.   Sponsored by SIA's <A HREF="sia01d.htm#RF">Regional Firms Committee</A>.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rgannon@sia.com>Rob Gannon</A> or <A HREF=mailto:pgoodbody@sia.com>Pim Goodbody</A></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="ira"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Retirement Conference</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>SIA is sponsoring the second Annual Retirement Conference to be held in Washington, D.C. from June5-6, 1997 at the JW Marriot Hotel.  The conference will center on the demographic, legislative  and regulatory trends affecting retirement products, social security, 401Ks, etc...  The conference will also focus on the opportunities about to unfold for the securities industry in general and firms in particular in helping clients reach their goals.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:gmonahan@sia.com>George Monahan</A></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="sales"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><STRONG>Retail Management Conference (Formerly Sales and Marketing Conference)</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>The Sales and Marketing Conference has been renamed the Retail Management Conference. This name change was done to more clearly reflect the content of the meeting, which addresses all of the very serious challenges and opportunities to be found in the retail segment of our industry.  This year's conference was held September 18-20, 1996 at the Intercontinental Hotel in Chicago, IL.   It is the principal conference of the year for sales and marketing managers and executives.  Next year's conference is scheduled for September 18-19, 1997 at the Disney Yacht & Beach Club in Orlando, FL.  Sponsored by SIA's <A HREF="sia01d.htm#SM">Sales and Marketing Committee</A>.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rthornblad@sia.com>Dick Thornblad</A></FONT><BR><BR>
