<HTML>
<TITLE>Roundtables</TITLE>
<body background="sia3abac.gif"><IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><B><I>Roundtables -- SIA Members Only</I></B></FONT><BR>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=4>
<FONT SIZE=3>Simply stated, a Roundtable is composed of 12-35 executives who are with different member firms and have essentially the same responsibilities.  The first SIA Roundtable began in 1976 when the CEOs from twelve regional firms came together for their first meeting.  Presently, 27 SIA Roundtable groups are now in operation.  SIA Roundtables meet for business discussions once or twice a year, and in addition, roundtable members often contact one another when faced with a problem or project where outside input is needed.
<P>
If you are with an SIA member firm and function in a role that corresponds to one of the groups indicated below, you are eligible to be considered for admission by the members of that group.  Please contact the staff adviser for more information.  If you have a suggestion for a new group, you may contact <A HREF=mailto:rgannon@sia.com>Rob Gannon</A>.</FONT>
<P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
