</TABLE><p>
<A NAME="A"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>Internet Access</FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>SIA now has a site on the World Wide Web aimed at enhancing communications with and among its members.  Coincident with the establishment of this Internet site, SIA entered into a relationship with  <A HREF="http://www.uu.net"><b>UUNET Technologies, Inc.,</b></A> UUNET is the leading provider of Internet access and is the official access provider to the Microsoft Network.  This special relationship provides our members and certain securities industry organizations with one source to turn to for all their Internet requirements: e.g., access, security products and services, web hosting and home page development -- all at specially reduced prices.  Contact:  <A HREF=mailto:pcassar@sia.com>Phyllis Cassar</font><p>
<A NAME="B"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>SIA Sprint Network Telecommunicatios</FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>Sprint, through its partnership with SIA, provides member firms with a full array of domestic and international telecommunications services.  The SIA Sprint Network, formed in 1990, currently has over 175 participating member firms and was designed to meet the needs of all SIA member firms: national, regional and local, by utilizing the group's purchasing power to leverage discounts based upon overall member participation.  Whether it be voice, data, video or multimedia services, the SIA Sprint Network can provide your firm with cost-effective and reliable communications services you need to be competitive in today's financial marketplace.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:atrager@sia.com>Art Trager</A></FONT><p>
<A NAME="E"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>New York City Area Private Network</FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>A consortium of large securities firms contracted with NYNEX in 1988 to create a voice and data communications network within New York City.  Over 23,000 voice and 3,000 data lines are currently operating on this network, saving participants money and providing reliable service.  Governance is provided via quarterly meetings of the more than 115 firms that are members of the consortium.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:pgoodbody@sia.com>Pim Goodbody</A></FONT><p>
<A NAME="I"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>Local Access Services</FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>In 1995, an agreement was signed with Teleport Communications Group (TCG) for providing local access communications services at attractive prices to SIA members and securities industry organizations in 37 major metropolitan areas throughout the U.S.  A key aspect of this agreement involves reaching certain activity levels during 1996.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:pgoodbody@sia.com>Pim Goodbody</A></FONT><p>
<A NAME="F"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>Rental Cars</FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>SIA provides discounts on cars rented from both Avis and Hertz.  The discounts are available for business and leisure travel for employees of members firms and their families.  An SIA discount card must be presented to receive the lower rate.  Discount cards, in unlimited supply, are available from SIA.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:atrager@sia.com>Art Trager</A></FONT><p>
<A NAME="H"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>Airlines</STRONG></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>SIA has made arrangements with both American and Delta Airlines to provide discounted airfares to and from SIA conferences.  Discounts will apply to the lowest applicable round trip fare, full first class or full coach fares, provided the passenger meets all tariff rules and restrictions.  Refer to conference brochures for specific instructions and appropriate SIA account numbers.  Fare are subject to limited availability and depend on the day/time of preferred travel.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:mgaul@sia.com> Melanie Gaul</A></FONT><p>
<A NAME="G"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>Shipping Services</STRONG></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>Through an agreement between SIA and Airborne Express, low cost and high quality service is provided to SIA members.   Airborne Express provides fast, reliable overnight delivery to virtually every zip code in the U.S. -- usually by 10:30 a.m. the next business morning -- plus, worldwide service to more than 200 countries.  They also provides flexible free pickup service from most locations during regular business hours.  Sky Courier is the crisis management service for those situations when "tomorrow" isn't fast enough!  This door-to-door next flight out service is available 24 hours a day, 365 days a year.  Members of SIA can save more than 15%, 30% and even 40% off the cost of Sky Courier's current rates.  Contact:<A HREF=mailto:pwilliams@sia.com> Phil Williams</A></FONT><p>
