<TITLE>Mgmt Development Programs</TITLE>
<body background="sia3abac.gif">
<IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><B><I>Management Development Programs</I></B></FONT><P><P>
<A NAME="wharton"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>Securities Industry Institute</FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>The Institute is a program consisting of on-campus courses and study for one week each March for three years.  It is designed for securities industry professionals who hold promise to be the leaders of tomorrow.  The program gives participants an in-depth understanding of the securities business and the environment in which firms operate.  The 1996 program was held March 10-15; 1997 program dates are March 9-14.   Contact: <A HREF=mailto:joneill@sia.com>Jack O'Neill</A></font><p>
<A NAME="branch"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>Branch Manager Development Program</FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>This three-day program brings together up to 24 branch managers per session for an intense examination of the knowledge, skills and attitudes relating to the core areas of management responsibility.  Segments of the program include goal setting, staffing, coaching and counseling, and marketing efforts.  An advanced session is available for more experienced managers to meet their unique needs and to help them continue their growth and development.  The programs can be conducted "in-house" for individual firms.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rthornblad@sia.com>Dick Thornblad</A></FONT><p>
<A NAME="brinstitute"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG>Branch Management Leadership Institute</FONT></STRONG><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>An intensive three-day program sponsored by SIA and the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania designed to meet the leadership-development needs of experienced, high-potential branch managers.  The inaugural session of the Branch Manager Leadership Institute was conducted June 2-5, 1996 at Wharton.  Tuition for this important program has been established at $1,800.  For more information, please feel free to contact <A HREF="mailto:dthornblad@sia.com">Dick Thornblad</A> at 212-618-0541.</FONT>
