<HTML>
<TITLE>SIA Stock Market Game</TITLE>
<body background="sia3abac.gif"><IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><B><I>The Stock Market Game </B></I></FONT><SUP><FONT SIZE=5><B><I>TM</I></B></FONT></SUP><BR>
<p><center><IMG SRC="siasmg2.gif"></center><p>
<FONT SIZE=3><A HREF=http://www.smg2000.org>The Stock Market Game</FONT> </A>
<SUP><FONT SIZE=1>TM</FONT></SUP> <FONT SIZE=3>(SMG), since its inception in 1977, is one of the most widely used classroom tools to teach basic economic concepts.  During the 1994/95 academic year, approximately 18,000 teachers in 49 states used the SMG in the classroom reaching over 600,000 students.<P>SMG is a ten-week simulation of Wall Street trading that provides a framework for teaching students in grades 4-12 about the American economic system.  SMG, offered during the fall and spring semesters, is designed for classroom use as a motivational tool to increase understanding of the stock market, the costs and benefits involved in economic decision-making, the sources and uses of capital and other related economic concepts.<P>SMG is an interdisciplinary teaching tool that allows teachers to create and direct learning in the classroom in a variety of disciplines.  In addition to the SMG Players Manual that is provided in a team kit and the donated materials, curriculuum materials with lesson plans and videos are also available.<P>During the ten week sessions, student teams invest a hypothetical $100,000 in common stocks on the New York and American stock exchanges and the NASDAQ Stock Market.  Teams submit their transactions daily and receive weekly portfolios highlighting their trades, current holdings, brokerage fees, margin interest and team ranking.  At the end of the ten week simulation, the winning teams are recognized with plaques, certificates, prizes and/or award ceremonies in their states.  In addition to competing based on the highest equity in portfolio, several states also offer essay contests and provide recognition and prizes for essay contest winners.<P>The  program is administered in 49 states by SMG Coordinators who are affiliated primarily with the National Council on Economic Education (NCEE) and its university based network of affiliated State Councils and Centers for Economic Education.  In several states local newspapers conduct SMG or work in conjunction with an NCEE affiliate.  SMG Coordinators conduct workshops for teachers prior to the ten week sessions.  These workshops present a basic understanding of the stock markets, how to play the SMG and an explanation of various economic concepts.<P>Although the SMG is designed for use in the classroom, many states have developed a program for adults to provide an increased awareness of the financial markets.<P>If you would like more information about The Stock Market Game </FONT><SUP><FONT SIZE=1>TM</FONT></SUP><FONT SIZE=3> or if you are a registered representative and available for classroom presentations, hosting office tours and sponsoring award ceremonies or other financial support to the SMG program in your area,  contact <A HREF="mailto:SIFEE@sia.com"> SIFEE@sia.com</A></FONT>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1><B>If you wish to obtain any of the following publications, please follow the instructions on the <A HREF="siapub11.htm">order form.</A></B><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1><FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Economic Education Annual Report</B></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>A summary of the activities of the Securities Industry Foundation for Economic Education, highlighting The Stock Market Game</FONT><SUP><FONT SIZE=1>TM</FONT></SUP><FONT SIZE=3> and how securities firms can become involved in economic education across the country. Free.  Contact:<A HREF="mailto:SIFEE@sia.com"> SIFEE@sia.com</A></FONT><P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1><FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>The Stock Market Game</B></FONT><SUP><FONT SIZE=2><B>TM</B></FONT></SUP><FONT SIZE=5><B> Video</B></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>This two part, 27-minute video provides a basic introduction on how The Stock Market Game </FONT><SUP><FONT SIZE=1>TM</FONT></SUP><FONT SIZE=3> (SMG) works. Part I, for teachers, is 14 minutes and Part II, for students, is 13 minutes. The video provides information about the SMG for teachers and students in a "fun and engaging" format, and addresses teacher's apprehensions about the stock market with testimonials from veteran teachers. Teachers and students who participate in the Game discuss SMG concurrently with the narrator's explanation of it providing an overview of the stock market and the American economic system. The video is also for securities industry professionals who want to learn more about the Game and how to get involved in their state's SMG program. $10. Contact:<A HREF="mailto:SIFEE@sia.com"> SIFEE@sia.com</A></FONT><P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1><FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Economics and The Stock Market Game </FONT><SUP><FONT SIZE=2>TM</FONT></SUP></B><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>Further enhancing the educational effectiveness of The Stock Market Game  </FONT><SUP><FONT SIZE=1>TM</FONT></SUP><FONT SIZE=3>, this classroom manual assists teachers in introducing students to the securities markets and to familiarizing them with a broad range of economic concepts.  Also applicable for some adult seminars on the securities industry. $15.  Contact:<A HREF="mailto:SIFEE@sia.com"> SIFEE@sia.com</A></FONT><P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1><FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>The Stock Market Game</B></FONT><SUP><FONT SIZE=2><B>TM</B></FONT></SUP><FONT SIZE=5><B> Guide: Classroom Activities</B></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>This teaching guide focuses upon simple lessons which incorporate fundamental concepts of the securities business with general economic concepts and puts them into a user-friendly format for classroom or seminar presentations. The lessons emphasize the direct connection between economics and the stock market by identifying and explaining relevant economic content. $15. Contact: <A HREF="mailto:SIFEE@sia.com"> SIFEE@sia.com</A></FONT><P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1><FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>In The News!</B></FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>A newsletter directed at teachers and students that focuses on current news events and their relationships to economics and the stock market. Free.  Contact:<A HREF="mailto:SIFEE@sia.com"> SIFEE@sia.com</A> or click here to view this year's <A HREF="smg02gg.htm">issues</A> in 'pdf' format.</FONT><P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1><FONT SIZE=3>&copy; 1997 Securities Industry Association</FONT>
