<HR NOSHADE=4><FONT SIZE=3>As specialists in the capital-raising process, foreign and domestic markets, and the impact of policies on them, SIA is eager to work with Congress and the administration to address the tremendous challenges our nation faces in the years ahead.  A potential crisis in financing the retirement of 76 million baby boomers, an aging infrastructure, skyrocketing health care and education costs, and increased global competition are but a few of the issues that loom over our economic future.<P>Briefing papers have been developed that summarize those public policy issues necessary to maintain the preeminence of the U.S. capital markets.  They include: <P><TABLE COLSPEC="L20">
