<title>Publications</title>
<BODY><body background="sia3abac.gif"><br>
<IMG SRC="sialog.gif" ALT="SIA"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><I><B>Publications</B></I></FONT>
<P>
<A NAME="Best"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Best Practices</B><BR>
<IMG SRC="bestprac.gif" ALT="Best Practices" BORDER=1 HSPACE=35 VSPACE=6 ALIGN=LEFT HEIGHT=175 WIDTH=90>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=3> Put the customer first.  This principle is the source of the trust and confidence that the securities industry has earned from the public and underlies the "best practices" compiled in this brochure.  The areas addressed by these best practices include client rights and responsibilities and guidance for compliance and sales management professionals.  This complimentary 19 page brochure will help guide firms and educate industry employees by bringing together the various best practices, individually endorsed by SIA's Board of Directors.  The diversity of firms may require each firm to accept, reject or modify these practices to suit each firm's particular characteristics.  Contact <A HREF="mailto:gcascio@sia.com">Geri-Anne Cascio</A>
<P>
<A NAME="Today"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Investment Today</B><p><FONT SIZE=3>
This is a newsletter designed for current and potential investors.  It deals with varied aspects of investing, includes a long-term perspective on securities ownership; information on the industry's commitment to investor education; and other useful ideas for investors.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:sserpico@sia.com>Suzanne Serpico</A>
<P>
<A NAME="Handbook"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Investor Education Handbook</B><BR>
<IMG SRC="handbook.gif" ALT="Investor Education Handbook" BORDER=1 HSPACE=35 VSPACE=6 ALIGN=LEFT HEIGHT=200 WIDTH=150>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=3>This comprehensive guide on investor education contains helpful suggestions on how you can fulfill your clients' and prospects' need for knowledge and information.  From development of a comprehensive educational "curriculum outline" to action-oriented education tips and techniques, this Handbook is designed to give you the guidance and resources you need to educate investors objectively and effectively.  The Handbook also includes ready-to-use seminar tips and more.  
<P>
Contact: <A HREF="mailto:gcascio@sia.com">Geri-Anne Cascio</A>
<P>
<BR>
<P>
<A NAME="Investor"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Investor Survey</B></FONT><P><FONT SIZE=3>The first annual <A HREF="sia06a1.htm"> SIA Investor Survey</A>, conducted by Yankelovich Partners and commissioned by the SIA, provides comprehensive opinion research of investor's attitudes toward the securities industry, brokerage services and investing in general.  A total of 1,505 investors were interviewed by telephone for their views on these and other matter including such policy issues as tax and retirement legislation.  Free copy available upon request.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rthornblad@sia.com>DickThornblad</A></FONT>
<P>
<A NAME="Topics"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Investor Topics</B></FONT><BR>
<IMG SRC="invstop.gif" ALT="Investor Topics" BORDER=1 HSPACE=35 VSPACE=6 ALIGN=LEFT HEIGHT=175 WIDTH=90>
<FONT SIZE=3>
<P><BR>
<I><B>Investor Topics</B></I> -- the latest educational initiative by SIA -- answers the most common questions new investors have.  SIA is offering the brochure to member firms for use as part of their client initiatives.  SIA strongly urges you to use Investor Topics as a low-cost, easy-to-read and follow tool to educate clients and prospects alike.  
<P>
To order <I><B>Investor Topics</B></I>, please use this <A HREF="sia06dd.htm">order form</A> or contact: <A HREF=mailto:sserpico@sia.com>Suzanne Serpico</A></FONT>
<P><BR><P>
<A NAME="Conduct"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Professional Conduct Program</B><BR>
<IMG SRC="prof2.gif" ALT="Professional Conduct Program" BORDER=1 HSPACE=35 VSPACE=6 ALIGN=LEFT HEIGHT=175 WIDTH=90>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=3>
This is a unique program designed to stimulate and shape the thought processes professionals in the securities industry use when faced with various ethical issues.  This program uniquely focuses on differing points of view surrounding "real-life" scenarios, drawn from actual member firm cases, and will provide users a new way to look at, think about and resolve issues.  The program is now available in 3.5" computer disk format and includes an introductory highlights video as well as a handbook for each participant.  To request a complimentary demonstration disk of the <I><B>Professional Conduct Program</B></I>, please contact: <A HREF=mailto:rthornblad@sia.com>Dick Thornblad</A>.  An <A HREF="profcond.htm">order form</A> is also available for your use.
<P><BR>
<A NAME="Guide"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Your Guide to Understanding Investing</B></FONT><BR>
<IMG SRC="yourgde.gif" ALT="Your Guide to Understanding Investing" BORDER=1 HSPACE=35 VSPACE=6 ALIGN=LEFT HEIGHT=190 WIDTH=115>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=3>
This is a 179-page investment primer containing information about investments and investing, including in-depth descriptions of the uses, risks and rewards of most investment products.  Written in plain English and fully illustrated, this book is an invaluable resource for your clients, prospects and employees.  It is excellent for use as a client gift, seminar leave-behind or prospecting tool and can be customized with your firm's identity and logo on the book cover.  
<P>
To order <I><B>Your Guide to Understanding Investing</B></I>, please use this <A HREF="yrguide.htm">order form</A> or contact: <A HREF=mailto:sserpico@sia.com>Suzanne Serpico</A></FONT>
<P><BR><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>&copy; 1997 Securities Industry Association
<A HREF="sia00.htm"><IMG Border=0 ALIGN=right SRC="siahome.gif" ALT="Homepage"></A>
