<HEAD>
<TITLE> SEC Final Rule </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<body background="sia3abac.gif">
<IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association">
<P>
<FONT  SIZE=+4><B><I>SEC Final Rule:</I></B></FONT>
<BR>
<FONT  SIZE=+3><I><B>Securities Transactions Exempt from Transactions Fees</B></I></FONT>
<P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=4>
<P>
The SEC recently adopted amendments to Rule 31-1 under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 and Rule 24e-2 under the Investment Company Act of 1940.  The purpose of these amendments is to conform these rules to recently enacted legislation that extends transaction fees to transactions in NASDAQ and other OTC securities  (other than bonds, debentures and other evidences of indebtedness) subject to prompt last-sale reporting.
<P>
Information relating to these rule changes are available through the <A HREF=http://www.sec.gov/rules/finrindx.htm>Securities and Exchange Commission</A>.
<P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>&copy; 1996 Securities Industry Association
