<HEAD>
<TITLE> Tax Reform </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<body background="sia3abac.gif">
<IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association"><BR><BR>
<FONT  SIZE=+3><B><CENTER>Securities Industry Benchmark Report on<BR>Tax Restructuring, 1993-1994</CENTER></B></FONT>
<P>
<BR>
<P>
<FONT  SIZE=+2><CENTER>Introduction</CENTER></FONT>
<P>
<HR NOSHADE=1>
<P>
The "Securities Industry Benchmark Report on Tax Restructuring, 1993-1994," compiled by Price Waterhouse LLP, summarizes the results of a survey conducted by SIA and PW.  The survey intended to analyze the effects of various tax restructuring proposals on securities industry companies.  A total of 12 companies responded to the survey and their aggregate data is represented in the results.
<P>
The 12 companies that responded to the survey have already received a more detailed version of the report that measures the impact of the various tax restructuring options for their individuals companies, and then compares those results against the aggregate data.
<P>
We think you will find the aggregate data quite interesting, comparing the corporate tax liabilities of the surveyed companies to what they would have paid under the tax restructuring options.  We are also very interested in broadening the survey.  The 12 companies accounted for nearly 40 percent of the industry net revenue and 50 percent of industry employment in 1994.
<P>
Those companies that did not respond to the survey but are still interested in participating in this analysis should contact <A HREF="mailto:peter_merrill@notes.pw.com">Peter Merrill</A> of Price Waterhouse at (202) 414-1666.  Also contact Peter if you have any questions or comments regarding the report, .
<P>
<HR NOSHADE=1>
Available for your review is the <A HREF="taxrfm.pdf">report on tax restructuring</A>.  This document is in 'pdf' format.  If your browser cannot read 'pdf' formatted documents,  you will need to download <A HREF="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/readstep.html">Adobe Acrobat Reader</A>.
<HR NOSHADE=1>
&copy; 1997 Securities Industry Association
