<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Year 2000 Sub-Committees </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<body background="sia3abac.gif">
<FONT SIZE=+4><B><EM><FONT  COLOR="#0000C0">Year 2000</FONT></EM></FONT>
<HR NO SHADE=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3>Year 2000 Sub-Committees</FONT></CENTER></B>
<HR NO SHADE=2>
<P>
<FONT  SIZE=+1><STRONG>Exchange and Utility Sub-Committee</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
<B>Mission:</B>  The Year 2000 Exchange and Utility Sub-Committee acts as the coordinator of year 2000 industry testing efforts among Exchanges, Clearing Corporations, and Depositories.  The role of the sub-committee is to:
<UL>
<LI>Define the strategy for street-wide industry testing, including participant and member roles, as an extension of individual product testing between specific utilities and members.
<LI>Develop the plan of action for implementing this testing strategy
<LI>Coordinate and facilitate this plan, while minimizing risk to all utilities, exchanges and participants
<LI>Interface with other sub-committee in achieving these goals.
</UL>
<P>
<FONT  SIZE=+1><STRONG>Third Party Software Sub-Committee</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
<B>Mission:</B>  The role of the Year 2000 Third Party Software Sub-Committee is to:
<UL>
<LI>Identify Year 2000 compliance issues and needs as they relate to third party software/hardware vendors.
<LI>Establish policies of 'best practices' in relation to Year 2000 contract and license agreements, legal aspects and issues of indemnity and/or risk in relation to third party vendors.
<LI>Identify vendor offerings, i.e. software, hardware, and services, to assist member organizations in third party vendor Year 2000 compliance.
</UL>
<P>
<FONT  SIZE=+1><STRONG>Data Providers Sub-Committee</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
<B>Mission:</B>  The role of the Year 2000 Data Providers Sub-Committee is to:
Define a common Year 2000 industry testing delivery schedule and vehicle for the data feeds necessary for DMD members' production environments.
Define and establish the data provider's role in Year 2000 street-wide indsutry testing effort.
Oversee and coordinate data providers responsibilities in Year 2000 compliance testing
Review and determine requirements for data format changes.
review, endorse and coordinate Year 2000 data format rollout plans and schedules.
<P>
<FONT  SIZE=+1><STRONG>Participant Street-Wide Testing Sub-Committee</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
<B>Mission: </B> The role of the Year 2000 Partcipants Street-Wide Testing Sub-Committee is to define needs, from a partcipant point of view, relative to:
<UL>
<LI>Year 2000 product testing
<LI>Year 2000 street-wide industry testing which will occur in 1999.
</UL>
In addition, this sub-committee will communicate these defined needs to other SIA-DMD testing sub-committees.
<P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
In addition to the SIA-DMD Year 2000 committees, NSCC/SIAC has formed the following committee to assist in their Year 2000 efforts:
<P>
<FONT  SIZE=+1><STRONG>Year 2000 Participant Advisory Committee</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
<B>Mission:</B>  The role of the NSCC.SIAC Year 2000 Participant Advisory Committee, relative to NSCC products and services, is to:
<UL>
<LI>Ensure that NSCC/SIAC Year 2000 compliance efforts and strategies will meet its participants' need in a reasonable and timely manner.
<LI>Review NSCC/SIAC's approach toward product and input/output data feeds and formats.
<LI>Endorse and participate in NSCC/SIAC product testing strategy.
</UL>
<P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
For more information on the Year 2000, check out:<P>
<UL>
<LH></LH>
<LI><A HREF="sia09zb.htm">Meeting Schedule & Summaries</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="sia09zc.htm">Year 2000 Survey</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="sia09za.htm"> Year 2000 Project Plan</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="sia09zd.htm">Testimony Before U.S. Congressional Subcommittee</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="sia09ze.htm">House Subcommittees Examine Federal and State Preparedness for Year 2000</A><P>
<LI>Additional Year 2000 sites include: <a href="http://www.year2000.com/cgi-bin/clock.cgi">Year 2000 Home Page</a> (sponsored by Peter deJager and The Tenagra Corporation); <a href="http://www.wa.gov:80/dis/y2000/y2000.htm">State of Washington</a> and <a href="http://www.itaa.org">Information Technology Association of America</a><P>
</UL>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
For more information, contact <A HREF="mailto:mtiernan@csfbg.csfb.com">Mike Tiernan</A>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
&copy; 1996 Securities Industry Association
