<TITLE>Data Management Division</TITLE>
<body background="sia3abac.gif"><IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><B><I> About The Data Management Division</I></B></FONT><BR><BR>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=4>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Mission</B></FONT><P>
The Data Management Division (DMD) is an organization whose sole purpose is to service the brokerage community.   DMD encompasses all phases of  <B> pre and post settlement trade clearance, information systems and data communications, </B>and is a necessary and respected arm of SIA. <P>DMD, in conjunction with various Advisory Groups, is instrumental in promoting uniformity of operational procedures and establishing a clear understanding of the requirements for the proper processing of our business transactions.  The close working relationship with these groups and other divisions of SIA enables the DMD to address the many challanges commonly encountered in our ever-changing industry.  DMD encourages its members to utilize their expertise and share ideas within the various committees.  Specific areas of concern are:<P>
<UL>
<LH></LH>
<LI>The development of efficient and uniform practices and procedures in all areas of the securities industry.<P>
<LI>The promotion of spirit, friendship and cooperation among members and member organizations.<P>
<LI>The welfare of our members.
</UL>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Government</B></FONT><P>
The government of the DMD is vested in a Governing Committee composed of the Officers and the Executive Committee, each chosen from members in good standing, and employed by a member firm of the Securities Industry Association. <P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Officers</B></FONT><P>
<CENTER><TABLE COLSPEC="L20 L20 L20" WIDTH=95%>
<TR VALIGN=TOP> <TD><STRONG>Officer</STRONG></TD><TD><STRONG>Affiliation</STRONG></TD> <TD><STRONG>Telephone</STRONG></TD></TR>
