<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Goals and Objectives: 1997 and Beyond</B></FONT><P>
<UL>
<LH></LH>
<LI>Bridge gap between end users and information technology<BR>
<LI>Client/Server technology<BR>
<LI>Continue advisory role on the Industry-Wide Glossary initiative and efforts concerning security descriptions standardization<BR>
<LI>Improve comparison process for NYSE equity "STEP OUT" transactions submitted in OCS (On-Line Comparison System)<BR>
<LI>Improve interface procedures among member firms, fund groups and related service organizations concerning mutual funds by representation on the ICI Broker Dealer Committee<BR>
<LI>Prepare for system implications of year 2000<BR>
<LI>Continue leading role in defining industry issues in use of the Internet
</UL>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Membership</B></FONT><P>
To join the DMD, please complete <A HREF="sia01fda.htm"> this application</A> and mail to: DMD, Financial Secretary, P.O. Box 567, Bowling Green Station, New York, NY 10274 or call 212-225-4374.<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Working Committees</B></FONT> <FONT SIZE=-1><B><EM>(* denotes Chairperson)</EM></B></FONT><P>
<STRONG><FONT SIZE=+1>Business Procedures</FONT></STRONG> --
Representation is across all firms.  It meets monthly to address current problems, concerns and future needs of the industry.  exchanges and regulatory agencies report on the current status of projects within their organizations.  <STRONG>Contacts:</STRONG><P>
<CENTER><TABLE COLSPEC="L20 L20 L20" BORDER=1 WIDTH=75%>
<TR><TD>Tom Quinn *</TD><TD>Merrill Lynch</TD><TD>201-557-2558</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Mike Canale</TD><TD>Pershing Division of DLJ</TD><TD>201-413-2990</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<STRONG><FONT SIZE=+1>Information Technology</FONT></STRONG> --
It is the intent of this working committee to promote an awareness in the membership regarding the development of new products.  Also, they bring the concerns and needs of the membership pertaining to the processing and distribution of information, including data communications, to the exchanges, regulatory agencies and the various vendors.  Meetings are held at least once a month to address issues of mutual concern. <STRONG> Contacts:</STRONG><P>
<CENTER><TABLE COLSPEC="L20 L20 L20" BORDER=1 WIDTH=75%>
<TR><TD>John Lauria *</TD><TD>Pershing Division of DLJ</TD><TD>201-413-3275</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>John Dolan</TD><TD>Merrill Lynch</TD><TD>201-557-3749</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
There are also three subcommittees charted to address specific areas of importance.  They are:<P>
<CENTER><TABLE COLSPEC="L20 L20 L20" BORDER=1 WIDTH=75%>
<TR><TD> <STRONG>Industry-Wide Glossary</STRONG></TD><TD>Les Sarter *</TD><TD>PaineWebber</TD><TD>201-902-6491</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><STRONG>Mutual Funds</STRONG></TD><TD>Steve Tunney *</TD><TD>Lewco Securities</TD><TD>201-524-8604</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><STRONG>Internet</STRONG></TD><TD>John Lauria *</TD><TD>Pershing Division of DLJ</TD><TD>201-413-3275</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<STRONG><FONT SIZE=+1><A HREF="sia09z.htm">Year 2000</A></FONT></STRONG> --
This <A HREF="sia09zf.htm">committee</A> was formed to investigate the impact the year 2000 will have on systems applications.  It disseminates applicable information among member firms, shares development of required tools, raises universal awareness and will assure industry-wide testing scheduled for early 1999.  <STRONG>Contacts:</STRONG><P>
<CENTER><TABLE COLSPEC="L20 L20 L20" BORDER=1 WIDTH=75%>
<TR><TD>Mike Tiernan *</TD><TD>CS First Boston</TD><TD>212-322-1938</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Mike Baxter</TD><TD>Morgan Stanley</TD><TD>212-762-2219</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Advisory Groups</B></FONT><P>
The DMD Advisory Groups consist of representation from: American Stock Exchange, Banks, Chicago Board of Options Exchange, Depository Trust Company, Government Securities Clearing Corporation, National Association of Securities Dealers, National Securities Clearing Corporation, New York Stock Exchange, Options Clearing Corporation, Securities Industry Automation Corporation.<P>
These Advisory Groups report internal developments on a monthly basis to the Executive Committee.  The Groups also work directly with  the Business Procedures and Information Technology Committees on an ongoing basis.
<P>
