<TITLE>Internal Audit Division</TITLE>
<body background="sia3abac.gif"><IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><B><I> About The Internal Auditors Division</I></B></FONT><BR><BR>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=4>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Mission</B></FONT><P>
The Internal Auditors Division (IAD) is a professional organization representing Internal Auditors from banks, broker-dealers, insurance companies, mutual funds, public accounting firms and self-regulatory agencies associated within the securities industry.  The IAD services its members in many ways by sponsoring educational seminars and courses covering topics of current interest to internal auditors and educational luncheons featuring distinguished industry leaders.  Publications dealing with auditing in the securities industry are emphasized in our Audit Guidelines covering the following Areas:
<UL>
<LH></LH>
<LI>Branch Offices<BR>
<LI>Commodities<BR>
<LI>Financial Issues<BR>
<LI>Operations<BR>
<LI>Trading Desks<BR>
<LI>Regulatory Issues<BR>
<LI>Systems Technology
</UL>
<P>
