<HTML>
<title>SIA Publications</title>
<BODY><body background="sia3abac.gif"><br>
<IMG SRC="sialog.gif" ALT="SIA"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><I><B>General Management</B></I></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Annual"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B><A HREF="siaan1.htm">Annual Report</A></B></FONT><BR>
<IMG SRC="siaar.gif" ALT="SIA Annual Report" BORDER=1 HSPACE=35 VSPACE=6 ALIGN=LEFT>A review of developments and issues in the past year, with emphasis on SIA advocacy activities at Federal and State levels, industry educational efforts and an updated summary of member services.  Other highlights include SIA's newly articulated <A HREF="sia06c.htm"> Values Statement</A> and a four-page Investor's <A HREF="#Today">Newsletter </A>insert for current and potential investors.  <P>Additional copies of the Annual Report can be ordered by contacting <A HREF=mailto:"jspellman@sia.com>Jim Spellman</A>
<P><P>
<A NAME="Brief"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Briefing Book</B></FONT><BR>
<IMG SRC="siabb.gif" ALT="SIA Briefing Book" BORDER=1 HSPACE=35 VSPACE=6 ALIGN=LEFT>SIA's staff biennially prepares the<I> Securities Industry Briefing Book</I> -- a publication to educate and explain the unique role of the securities industry in the U.S. economy. The book contains sections describing the industry and its functions as well as background and reasons for implementing sound policies to maintain the preeminence of the U.S. capital markets.<P> It is distributed to all members of Congress, administration officials, regulators, and member firms to use with Senators and Representatives, local policy makers, schools, and other community constituents.  No charge.  
<P>Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rpepe@sia.com> Rosalie Pepe</A><P>
<A NAME="Info"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Infopack Service for Non-Members</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>This service is designed to help individuals not with SIA member organizations but who are associated with the securities industry to keep abreast of events and developments occurring within the industry. Infopack consists of a steady stream of bulletins, reports and other releases, as well as notices of conferences and seminars. The charge is $175 per year. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rpepe@sia.com>Rosalie Pepe</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Key"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Keyman Subscription Service</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>Throughout the year a variety of SIA mailings are made expressly to the managing executive in each member organization. These mailings include legislative reports, special bulletins, position papers and other releases of  importance to top management. Others within the firm who wish to receive duplicate copies of these mailings may have their names added to a keyman subscription list. An annual charge of $100 for members applies to each such name to defray costs. Simply write the Association in New York, enclosing a check.  <BR>Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rpepe@sia.com> Rosalie Pepe</A></FONT>
<P>
<A NAME="Year"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Securities Industry Yearbook</B></FONT><P><IMG SRC="siayear.gif" ALT="SIA Yearbook" HSPACE=35 VSPACE=6 BORDER=1 ALIGN=LEFT><FONT SIZE=3> An invaluable reference of over 900 pages for people involved in the securities industry. Includes detailed information on individual firms, such as key personnel and department heads, number of customer accounts, registered representatives and offices, capital, underwriting volume, syndications and much more. Also provides rankings by capital, offices, employees and RRs. Additional sections present industry facts and comprehensive industry and market statistics.  
<P><BR><P>The 1995-96 edition is $85 for members, and $125 for non-members.  The 1996-97 edition will be published August 1996 and the price will remain the same.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rpepe@sia.com>Rosalie Pepe</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Source"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Sources:</B> </FONT><FONT SIZE=4><B><I>The Securities Executive's Guide to Products and Services</I></B></FONT><P>
<IMG SRC="sourcesb.gif" ALT="Sources" HSPACE=45 VSPACE=6 BORDER=1 ALIGN=LEFT><FONT SIZE=3>This directory is a comprehensive, classified buyer's guide expressly designed to assist securities firm executives in their search for sources of products/services.  The directory consists of listings and display ads covering over 90 different categories from accounting firms and clearing houses to training organizations and video producers. <P>Distribution of the 1996-97 edition will be made, free of charge, in April to managing executives and department heads of member firms.  Extra copies are available for $5 each. <p> Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rpepe@sia.com>Rosalie Pepe</A></FONT><BR><P><BR>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
<B>To order any of the above publications, please follow <A HREF="siapub11.htm">order form</A> instructions.</B>
