<HTML><BODY>
<title>Publications</title>
<body background="sia3abac.gif"><br>
<IMG SRC="sialog.gif" ALT="SIA"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><I><B>Legal and Legislative</B></I></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="Capitol"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>The Capitol Chronicle</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>A bi-weekly newsletter informing members of major legislative and regulatory developments in Washington of particular significance to our industry.  Published during the congressional sesion. No charge. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:erives@sia.com>Elizabeth Rives</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="State"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Stateview</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>A periodic discussion of key legislative and regulatory issues on the state level which are of particular significance to our industry. No charge. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:states@sia.com>Jim Everett</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Alert"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Legal Alert</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>Issued as needed, to alert SIA members to significant regulatory and legal developments that may require their immediate attention. $50 per year; non-members $75.  Contact Office of General Counsel</FONT><P>
<A NAME="Grass"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>SIA on the Hill: A Grassroots Report</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>A monthly newsletter updating the Grassroots Network on government relations and political activities. Keeps the network informed of legislative initiatives and what it can do to help. Published during the congressional session. Sent to each member of the Grassroots Network. No charge. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:dmiller@sia.com>Dianne Miller</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Legis"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Legislative Alert</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>A timely publication sent to the Grassroots network when a key congressional vote is imminent. Alerts encourage members to contact their congressmen and senators and urge support or opposition to the legislation. No charge. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:smorgan@sia.com>Suzanne Morgan</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Position"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>SIA Position Papers</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>Brief issue papers outlining background and SIA position on legislation affecting the securities industry. Issued to Board of Directors, Government Representatives, Government Relations and other SIA committees. Distributed to key government representatives on a periodic basis. No charge. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:erives@sia.com>Elizabeth Rives</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Reg"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Regulatory Review</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>A quarterly publication which reviews rules adopted and proposed during the quarter by the SEC, Amex, NASD and NYSE. This publication is included in the Legal Alert subscription. Contact Office of General Counsel</FONT><P>
<A NAME="Congress"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Guide to the U.S. Congress</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>This alphabetical listing of the members of Congress includes pictures, bios and committee memberships. Presented in a new and different format, it is a must for anyone interested in the U.S. Congress. Cost is $10. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:mkappa@sia.com>Mary Kappa</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Litrep"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Litigation Report</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>Issued approximately ten times a year as needed outlining litigation and arbitration issues with a view towards helping members defend such actions.  This publication is included in the Legal Alert subscription.  Contact Office of General Counsel.</FONT><P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
<B>To order any of the above publications, please follow <A HREF="siapub11.htm">order form</A> instructions.</B>
