<TITLE>Internet Update Conference</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<!-- Generation of PM publication page 1 -->
<body background="sia3abac.gif">
<IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association">
<P>
<FONT  SIZE=+2 COLOR="red"><B><BLINK><FONT  SIZE=+3>P</FONT>lease <FONT  SIZE=+3>N</FONT>ote<BR><FONT  SIZE=+3>D</FONT>ate <FONT  SIZE=+3>C</FONT>hange</BLINK></B></FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><B>(SIA Members Only)</B><BR>
<FONT  SIZE=+4><B>INTERNET UPDATE CONFERENCE</B></FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<FONT  SIZE=+1><CENTER>Monday  February 3, 1997<BR>
New York Marriott Marquis Hotel<BR>
1535 Broadway (between 45th and 46th Streets)</CENTER></FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><B>Co-Sponsored by:</B><BR>
<I>Technology Regulatory Subcommittee of the SIA Ad Hoc Technology Issues Committee<BR>
SIA Technology Management Committee</I></CENTER>
<P>
The regulatory framework and the utilization of the Internet and related technologies by the securities industry continue to evolve at a rapid pace.  The purpose of this special Conference, for SIA members and securities industry organizations only, is to provide an update on both the regulatory and application areas.  This will include the opportunity for attendees to raise questions and issues with key regulators and with representatives of securities firms that are utilizing the Internet for critical business applications.  You will want to ensure your firm is represented.
<P>
<HR NOSHADE=1>
