<HTML>
<title>Publications</title>
<BODY><body background="sia3abac.gif"><br>
<IMG SRC="sialog.gif" ALT="SIA"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><I><B>Industry Data & Analysis</B></I></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="Data"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Securities Industry DataBank</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3> This service consists of a comprehensive database containing aggregated financial  and employment data contained in the quarterly FOCUS Report income statements and balance sheets filed by all NYSE broker-dealers dealing with the public.  Available on 3.5 inch IBM or Mac-compatible diskettes in EXCEL spreadsheet format.  This industry data is aggregated into 17 firm categories including: national full line firms, large investment banks, regionals, discounters, clearing firms, etc.  Database subscription for most recent four quarters costs $1,200 for SIA and NYSE members; $2,400 for non-members. For further details, contact: <A HREF=mailto:gmonahan@sia.com>George Monahan</A> or <A HREF=mailto:gtoto@sia.com>Grace Toto</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Trend"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Securities Industry Trends</B></FONT><P>
<A HREF=trends.htm><IMG SRC="trends.gif" ALT="SIA Trends" BORDER=1 HSPACE=35 VSPACE=6 ALIGN=LEFT></A>
<FONT SIZE=3>A periodic report discussing profitability and financial statements of the securities industry; key revenue sources and expenses of securities firms; coverage of tax law changes and economic developments affecting securities firms, trends in international finance, and other topics vital to securities firm management. Yearly subscription is $75; $125 for non-members. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:gmonahan@sia.com>George Monahan</A> or <A HREF=mailto:gtoto@sia.com>Grace Toto</A></FONT><P>
<B>1996 Issues:</B>
<dd>Review of Economic, Legislative and Regulatory Issues in the U.S. Capital Markets During 1995  (May)
<dd>Finishing Strong: 1995 Securities Industry Performance: Highlights  (March)<P>
<B>1995 Issues:</B>
<dd> Third Quarter Makes the Year -- 1995 Securities Industry Performance   (December)
<dd>Tax Reform: An Introduction  (October)
<dd>The Effectiveness of Saving Incentives: A Review of the Evidence  (October)
<dd>Industry Rebound Underway -- 1994-95 Securities Industry Performance  (July)
<dd>Quick Review of the Case for Lower Capital Gains Taxes  (April)
<dd>Primer on Corporate Finance in 1994 -- "Down But Not Out" (April)
<dd>SIA's Blueprint for Reviving the Savings Ethic  (March)
<dd>An Update on Industry Trends (January)<P>
<A NAME="Profit"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Profitability Report</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>Through this service,  80 participating SIA member firms receive quarterly information on how their profitability compares with other firms and how they trend on a quarter-to-quarter basis.  Participants are grouped by size of firm and ranked within their subgroup as well as overall.  Participants range in size from small local firms to the very largest regional firms.  The report includes information on pre-tax return on equity, profit margin on gross and net revenues, pre-tax profit, gross revenues and equity capital.  Complete confidentiality is preserved.  Cost is $200 per year. Detailed information available upon request. <B>For SIA members only.</B> Contact <A HREF=mailto:mdevito@sia.com>Michele DeVito</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Fact"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Securities Industry Fact Book</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>An annual statistical guide offering decades of data covering global and domestic capital markets and the securities industry in general. The 1996 edition provides nearly 100 pages of tables and charts on various aspects of the securities industry including: underwriting; private placements; M&A; securities industry revenue, costs, profits and employment; discounters; NYSE, Amex and Nasdaq statistics; individual investor statistics, international data, economic statistics, and much more. Cost is $45; $90 for non-members.   For an additional $20, data is available on 3.5 inch diskettes in EXCEL spreadsheet format.   Contact: <A HREF=mailto:gmonahan@sia.com>George Monahan</A> or <A HREF=mailto:gtoto@sia.com>Grace Toto</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Eco"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Securities Industry's Economic Impact on New York State & City  -- 1996 Update</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>This study shows the New York securities industry's significant impact on the State and City economies.  Areas covered include: employment; taxes; New York business; commercial real estate; philanthropic activities; capital raising for business and government.  Cost is $30 for members; $50 for non-members.   Contact: <A HREF=mailto:gmonahan@sia.com>George Monahan</A></FONT><P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
<B>To order any of the above publications, please follow <A HREF="siapub11.htm">order form</A> instructions.</B>
