<title>SIA Publications</title>
<BODY><body background="sia3abac.gif"><br>
<IMG SRC="sialog.gif" ALT="SIA"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><I><B>Local Firms</B></I></FONT><P>
<A NAME="LFNETWK"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Local Firms Business Networking Opportunities Directory</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>The main purpose of this directory is to help local firms identify potential business partners in one, easy to use reference source.  The directory is a compilation of local firm profiles and each profile includes: a lead contact,; narrative descriptions of the firm and its business; descriptions of products and services offered to other local firms; listing of business opportunities that a firm is seeking from other local firms; checklists that identify the firm by type of business; a breakdown of firm products and services by percentage of total revenue; and firm demographics and professional activities.  The directory also includes handy cross-references to find potential business partners quickly.   Copies are available at $50 each for members and $100 each for non-members.  Contact <A HREF=mailto:rgannon@sia.com>Rob Gannon</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="LFRR"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Report on Local Firm RRs: Recruiting, Training, Performance and Compensation</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>This 1995 survey contains benchmarks for recruiting, training, performance and compensation of smaller broker-dealers.  Cost is $50 per report for members; $100 for non-members. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:rgannon@sia.com>Rob Gannon</A></FONT><P>
