<HTML>
<title>SIA Publications</title>
<body background="sia3abac.gif"><br>
<IMG SRC="sialog.gif" ALT="SIA"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+4><I><B>Management Surveys</B></I></FONT><BR><BR>
<A NAME="Pract"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Employee Benefits Practices</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>This report contains information on health insurance, dental insurance, disability coverage, life insurance, accidental death and dismemberment, travel accident, retirement plans, sick days/personal days, vacation policy, employee assistance programs, flexible benefits and other miscellaneous practices including severance pay, annual physicals, etc.  Data for 1995 is scheduled to be available by second quarter 1996.  The previous study was conducted in 1993.  The cost of the study ranges from $315-$745 per copy for members, based on the number of employees; non-members can obtain a copy of this report for $1,425.  Purchasers and participants can obtain additional copies for $50 each. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:scarlson@sia.com>Steve Carlson</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Salary"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Office Salaries in the Securities Industry</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>This annual SIA clerical compensation study includes base salary and bonus statistics on 100 non-exempt positions in areas such as Administration and Finance, Compliance, Operations, Sales and Systems.  The 1995 study contains 500 pages of statistics provided by 57 SIA member firms employing approximately 120,000 individuals and compares 1995 weekly salaries to 1994 (and 1994 bonuses) for 37 major metropolitan areas.  Participants are grouped into four segments based on employment and the study presents average, median, 10th, 25th, 75th and 90th percentile figures for each position in each metropolitan area.  The cost for the study ranges from $500-$740 per report for members based on number of employees; non-members can obtain a copy of this report for $1,425.  Purchasers and participants can obtain additional copies for $75 each. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:scarlson@sia.com>Steve Carlson</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Earn"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Management and Professional Earnings in the Securities Industry</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>This annual comprehensive study is based on data submitted by SIA member firms employing over 100,000 individuals, with data on four industry segments based on total employment.  The report contains compensation data for 137 management positions within 10 major categories.  This 700 page report contains current and previous year salary and bonus information for New York City and non-New York City based employees.  Calculations are provided for average, median, 10th, 25th, 75th and 90th percentiles.  The cost for the study ranges from $500-$740 per report for members based on number of employees; non-members can obtain a copy of this report for $1,425.  Purchasers and participants can obtain additional copies for $75 each.  Contact: <A HREF=mailto:scarlson@sia.com>Steve Carlson</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Screen"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1</A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>RR Screening Test Service</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>The SIA's RR Screening Test is designed as a pre-employment paper and pencil test predictive of an RR trainee candidate's ability to learn the kinds of material necessary to successfully complete the Series 7 examination. The test is widely used by firms as a screening device prior to hiring RR trainees and has proven effective in avoiding hiring mistakes. Firms are assessed a quarterly fee of $20/person taking a Series 7 test. Fee is discounted dependant on number people taking test. It does not matter how many of the SIA tests a firm administers. The fee is calculated only on the basis of the number of people actually taking a Series 7 test. Literature is available on request. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:pfaber@sia.com>Pam Faber</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Turn"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Employee Turnover 1992-1993</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>This study details employee turnover rates and reasons for turnover in 1992 and the first six months of 1993. Data are supplied by twenty-four SIA member firms employing approximately 98,000 individuals.  The report summarized the data for three employee groups: non-exempt employees, exempt employees and registered representatives.   The cost for this study is $200 per copy for members; $450 for non-members; $50 for firms that supplied data. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:scarlson@sia.com>Steve Carlson</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Budget"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Budgeted Salary and Bonus Increases</B></FONT><p><FONT SIZE=3>This annual study provides firms with a measure of much salaries and bonuses are expected to increase in the coming year.  The report presents actual and estimated percentages budgeted for salary and bonus increases for exempt and non-exempt personnel.  Data are presented in arrays and averages are "weighted" based on the number of individuals involved.  The cost of the study is $40 per report for members; $50 per report for non-members. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:scarlson@sia.com>Steve Carlson</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Prod"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"><B>Production and Earnings of RRs</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>This annual survey provides over 100 pages of information on retail and institutional registered representatives' production, earnings and payouts as well as average ticket sizes.  Average and median data are provided for six industry segments based on the number of brokers employed.  Individual firm data is also provided on a non-identifying basis.  Also included are three-year historical trends and data on production, earnings, and training costs of newly-registered retail RRs.  The cost for the study ranges from $320-$715 per report for members based on the number of RRs; non-members can obtain a copy of this report for $1,425.  Purchasers and participants can obtain additional copies for $60 each. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:scarlson@sia.com>Steve Carlson</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Prices"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Prices Charged Retail Clients</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>This study details securities firms retail pricing in nearly 300 pages of data, tables and charts.  Information is provided for individual participants (non-identifying) as well as in four different segments based on number of brokers employed.  It includes: stock and option comission grids; low, median and high commission charges; discounting policies; IRA; Keogh and other self-directed account set-up and maintenance fees; margin rates charged based on debit balance groupings, and wrap account policies.  Conducted approximately every three years, the latest study (1993 data), will be updated during the first half of 1996 to reflect 1995 retail pricing.  This study is an indispensable tool for firms that wish to take competitive factors into account in evaluating or adjusting their own pricing practices.  The cost for the study ranges from $32 to $700 per report for members based on the number of RRs, non-members can obtain a copy of this report for $1,425.  Purchasers and participants can obtain additional copies for $50 each. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:scarlson@sia.com>Steve Carlson</A></FONT><P>
<A NAME="Top Mgmt"><HR NOSHADE SIZE=1></A>
<FONT SIZE=5><IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <B>Compensation of Top Management in Local and Regional Firms</B></FONT><p>
<FONT SIZE=3>This report  covers calendar years 1992 and 1993 and is based on data from 52 local and regional firms employing approximately 25,000 individuals.  The report provides specific information on total compensation, including base salary, bonus and commission.  In addition, where applicable, it includes data on profit sharing and long term compensation.  The study also provides a summary of executive perquisites for certain positions  The cost for the study ranges from $160 to $480 per copy for members depending on gross revenues, non-members can obtain a copy of this report for $1,425.  Purchasers and participants can obtain additional copies for $60 each. Contact: <A HREF=mailto:scarlson@sia.com>Steve Carlson</A></FONT><P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1><B>To order any of the above publications, please follow <A HREF="siapub11.htm">order form</A> instructions.</B>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>&copy; 1997 Securities Industry Association
