<TITLE>Press Release </TITLE>
<body background="sia3abac.gif"><IMG SRC="siaband.gif" ALT="Securities Industry Association"><P>
For Release: <STRONG>Thursday, October 31, 1996</STRONG>
<P>				
Contact:
<dd><A HREF="mailto:jspellman@sia.com">James D. Spellman</A>
<dd>(202) 296-9410								
<dd><A HREF="mailto:mdraper@sia.com">Margaret Draper</A>
<dd>(212) 618-0531
<P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=6><B>SIA to Sponsor Internet Update Conference</B></FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><FONT  SIZE=5><B>Hardwick Simmons to Deliver Keynote Address <BR>in New York City, February 4</B></FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<dd><STRONG>New York, NY</STRONG> -- The Securities Industry Association is sponsoring an <A HREF="sia02b.htm#net">Internet Update Conference</A> that will update professionals from its member firms on the latest developments in the regulation and use of the Internet and related new technologies.
<P>
<dd>The conference, organized by the association's Technology Regulatory Subcommittee of the Ad Hoc Technology Issues Committee and the Technology Management Committee, will be held all day Tuesday, February 4, 1997, at the Marriott Marquis Hotel in New York City.
<P>
<dd>Hardwick Simmons, president and chief executive officer of Prudential Securities Incorporated, will keynote the conference, sharing his perspective on the potentials and issues presented by the new technologies, as well as the challenges a securities firm faces in using the Internet.
<P>
<dd>Other highlights will include:
an overview of the regulatory and compliance environment for Internet usage.
a panel discussion on regulatory issues with representatives of the regulatory agencies and self-regulatory organizations.
a presentation and panel showcasing how securities firms are using Internet technologies, and
workshops on:  regulatory and compliance issues, what the Internet offers, lessons learned from the early adopters of the new technologies, and implementing email between registered representatives and customers.
<P>	
<dd>For registration, hotel and other information, contact Mary Ann Battista at (212) 618-0577, email:  mbattista@sia.com, or visit SIA's home page at http://www.sia.com.
<P>
<dd>Registration is limited to employees of SIA member firms and regulatory, clearing and depository organizations.
<P>
<dd>The Securities Industry Association brings together the shared interests of 750 securities firms throughout North America to accomplish common goals.  SIA members -- including investment banks, broker-dealers, specialists, and mutual fund companies -- are active in all markets and in all phases of corporate and public finance.  In the U.S. SIA members collectively account for approximately 90 percent, or $100 billion, of securities firms' revenues and employ about 350,000 individuals.  They manage the accounts of more than 50-million investors directly and tens of millions of investors indirectly through corporate, thrift and pension plans.  
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
&copy; 1996 Securities Industry Association
