<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>SIA Statement in Reaction to Today's SEC, NASD Settlement</B></FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<dd><STRONG>New York, NY</STRONG>,  -- The Securities Industry Association today released the following statement in response to the Securities and Exchange Commission's settlement with the National Association of Securities Dealers regarding the regulation of The Nasdaq Stock Market:
<P>
<dd>Today's agreement between the Securities and Exchange Commission and the National 
<dd>Association of Securities Dealers marks another step in ongoing efforts to continue to 
<dd>improve our markets to ensure that they are the world's most liquid and best capitalized 
<dd>with tough, effective regulations and surveillance to protect investors.  Enhancing the public's 
<dd>trust and confidence in our financial markets is a priority for the securities industry, and we 
<dd>are committed to doing whatever we can in this regard. 
<P>
<dd>The U.S. capital markets are the world's envy.  In no other country are there three major 
<dd>national stock markets competing for issuers and investors.  That competition helps drive 
<dd>continuing improvements in the services our markets provide.  High standards of 
<dd>professionalism and state-of-the-art technologies are two of the many hallmarks that 
<dd>distinguish our capital markets worldwide.
<P>
The Securities Industry Association brings together the shared interests of more than 750 securities firms throughout North America to accomplish common goals.  SIA members -- including investment banks, broker-dealers, specialists, and mutual fund companies -- are active in all markets and in all phases of corporate and public finance.  In the U.S., SIA members collectively account for approximately 90 percent, or $100 billion, of securities firms' revenues and employ about 350,000 individuals.  They manage the accounts of more than 50-million investors directly and tens of millions of investors indirectly through corporate, thrift and pension plans.
