<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Sen. Roth, Financial Services Industry Executives to Release <BR>New Survey on IRAs, Thursday, May 16<P>Press Conference To Draw Attention on Need to Enact IRAs<P></B></FONT></CENTER>
<STRONG>Washington, DC</STRONG>,  --  Sen. William V. Roth (R-Del.) and other members of Congress who have supported legislation to enact tax incentives for Individual Retirement Accounts (IRAs) will join members of the Savings Coalition to release a new survey on the public's assessment of IRAs. <P>
<STRONG>The Press Conference will beheld on Thursday, May 16, at 10 a.m. in Room 215 of the Dirksen Senate Office Building.</STRONG><P>
The survey is being done by pollsters Frank Luntz and Celinda Lake, who will release the results at the press conference.  The survey will report on the popularity of IRAs and the impact that more IRA incentives would have on Americans' retirement savings patterns.<P>
Others scheduled to participate are: Sens. John Breaux (D-La.) and Kay Bailey Hutchison (R-Tx.); Rep. Richard E. Neal (D-Mass.); and representatives from: American Council on Education; Citizens for a Sound Economy; Dean Witter, Discover & Co.; Fidelity; Independent Bankers Association; Institute of Electrical & Electronics Engineers; International Association for Financial Planning; Investment Company Institute; Merrill Lynch & Co.; National Association of Home Builders; Securities Industry Association; and U.S. Chamber of Commerce.<P> 
The Savings Coalition of America was established in 1991 to support incentives to increase personal savings in the U.S.  Its main objective is to win passage of expanded IRA legislation by the U.S. Congress and signed by the President.<P>
