Concluded at the meeting:<P> 
<UL>
<LH></LH>
<LI>It was announced that the SIA Operations Committee will form a Year 2000 Subcommittee to assist in the formulation of test criteria to ensure Year 2000 compliance by member firms<BR>  
<LI>SIA will create an Internet Website for Year 2000<BR>
<LI>As of the meeting, 23 Firms responded to the Year 2000 Survey distributed to the DMD membership.  DMD member lists were distributed to volunteers from the committee members to solicit participation from non-respondents<BR>
<LI>The final draft version of the Year 2000 Project Plan was presented to the Committee.  The Committee will vote on Plan acceptance at the September 26 meeting<BR>
<LI>The shortage of UNIX-based analysis tools was noted.  Anyone having knowledge of such tools was asked to inform the committee<BR>
<LI>The Committee received status reports from the following Year 2000 coordinators from outside agencies and exchanges on their Year 2000 preparations:
</UL>
<P>
<dd><STRONG>SIAC & NSCC </STRONG>(Post Trade)<P>	
1. SIAC will be flexible in terms of user requirements and support six or eight character dates.  Firms may be permitted to convert date formats at their convenience, i.e., there will be no fixed, streetwide conversion date<BR>
2. NSCC has established a Year 2000 working committee<BR>
3. SIAC & NSCC have identified issues unique to their application as they relate to date processing<BR>
4. SIAC & NSCC are in the process of completing a document defining application development standards for Year 2000 compliance<BR>
5.  SIAC & NSCC are preparing a Year 2000 project plan<BR>
6. There will be a separate project plan for Participant Testing.  The testing will be on a manageable scale and conducted in early 1999<P>
<dd><STRONG>SIAC</STRONG> (Trading)<P>
1. Ken  Miller distributed a summary project plan for "NYSE/AMEX Year 2000 Trading."  Trading and post trading are coordinating their efforts.  IDC and OCS activities are included in their plan.<P>  
<dd><STRONG>DTC</STRONG><P>
1. DTC will have all dates represented in 8 character format by the end of 1998.<BR>
2. With respect to record layouts affecting DTC clients, FILLER fields may be used to accommodate expanded dates.  With respect to transmission record lengths, even if the record length is increased because of 8 character dates, DTC clients will still be permitted to specify the length of records transmitted from DTC to the client.<P>
<dd><STRONG>GSCC</STRONG><P>
1. GSCC believes all their internal systems are Y2K compliant.<BR>
A. Dates are maintained in GSCCs system in Julian date format (YYYYDDD) encoded as an integer - this value is used for all calculations, deltas and sorts.<BR>
B. GSCC properly handles the Year 2000 leap year.<BR>
C. All screen displays contain 8 character date fields (MM/DD/YYYY) <BR>
D. Input data formats specify 8 character dates for trade date and settlement date.  The DataTrak header record has a date format of MMDDYY which requires further investigation<BR>
E. The output formats specify 10 character dates as MM/DD/YYYY for trade date and settlement date.  The Autoroute output header contains a Date/Time stamp in the form  DD-MMM-YYYYHH:SS.HH<BR>
2. Externally, GSCC is awaiting a decision by their clearing agent (Chase/Chemical) regarding the use of 6 or 8 character dates<P>
<dd><STRONG>CBOE</STRONG><P>
1. CBOE has begun the process of upgrading their systems to be Year 2000 compliant.  It initially estimates that 4 man-years of work will be required for Year 2000 compliance. They are auditing current applications and Third party software.  CBOE is asking every department to review/test all software/hardware components for potential problems.<BR>
2. CBOE clients having access to CBOE databases to create ad hoc reports will be polled with respect to their preference regarding 6 or 8 character date formats. <BR>
3. CBOE is preparing an RFP to be presented to various consulting firms in order to select one to help with the initial phases of the Y2K project. <P>
Additional agencies and exchanges will be scheduled for future Committee meetings.  Committee members have been asked to provide Mike Tiernan with names of other agencies which should be invited.
<P>
<IMG SRC="goldball.gif"> <STRONG><A NAME="sep26">September 26, 1996</A></STRONG>
<P> 
