<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>CAT Division News</TITLE>
<body background="sia3abac.gif">
<p>
<center><font size=+2><b><em>CAT DIVISION NEWS</em></b></font></center>
<p>
<b><font size=+1>Rewrite still on track</font></b>
<p>
<dd>The rewrite of the ACATS system is progressing slightly ahead of schedule with target implementation date for the project remaining June 1998. The National Securities Clearing Corporation (NSCC) prepared and  distributed its Concept Paper to the Advisory Committee and is currently drafting a business plan.
<p>
<dd>Thomas McCarthy, Vice-President/Director of NSCC Operations, discussed findings of the five individual Focus Groups. The Focus Groups addressed product redesign, technology and new member issues in the rewrite process. The five focus groups are addressing:
<p>
<ul>
<li>Product Enhancement
<li>Banking
<li>International 
<li>Mutual Funds
<li>Domestic Linkages
</ul>
<p>
Proposed changes include: 
<p>
<ul>
<li>Creating three days of  "Request" status, replacing the current NEW status.
<li>Two days of "Review," replacing the current PEND status.
<li>Eliminating "Settlement 1" from the current cycle.
<li>Initiating requester assigned control numbers.
<li>Providing functionality to make ACATS an on-line, interactive service.
</ul>
<p>
Additional recommendations include:
<p>
<ul>
<li>Reducing the number of receive and deliver tickets currently generated in ACATS.
<li>Identifying assets eligible at DTC but not CNS eligible.
<li>Forwarding a deliver order to DTC.
<li>Providing CNS eligibility for municipal bonds, corporate bonds and unit investment trusts.
<li>Providing system enhancements to accommodate partial transfers, automate fail reversals, reclaims,   custody redeliver and accelerate residual credit processing.
<li>Accomplishing foreign asset processing via use of ISIN's  identification number, which will ease           the pricing of foreign assets.
<li>Including government linkages via Government Securities Clearing Corporation (GSCC) for treasuries and Participants Trust Company for mortgage-backed assets.
</ul>
<p>
To become a member of the CAT Division, please complete this <a href="sia01ffa.htm">application</a> or call Jack Mills at (303)969-4358. 
<p>
 If you have any comments or questions about the CAT Division, please e-mail <A HREF="mailto:jack_mills@ml.com">Jack Mills</A>.
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>&copy; 1997 Securities Industry Association
