<html>
<head>
<title>Professor Kent Udell</title>
</head>
<body background="../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif">
<center><h1>Kent Udell</h1><p>
<img src="../../../BERC/Gallery/KentBW.jpg" border = "2"></center>
<hr>
</center>
<h4>
Kent S. Udell is a full professor in both the Department of Mechanical Engineering and the Department of Civil Engineering at the University of California at Berkeley.  He is the Director of the Berkeley Environmental Restoration Center and Principal Investigator for the UC-Navy Fast-Track Clean-up contract to bring innovative technologies from UC Berkeley, Lawrence 
Berkeley National Laboratory, and the Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory to the clean-up of NAS Alameda.  He is widely recognized for his research in multiphase heat and mass transfer in porous media, particularly in the area of in-situ soil and groundwater remediation.  He is generally credited as the pioneer of steam injection as a viable technique for the in-situ remediation of sites contaminated with volatile NAPLs.  His contribution was central to the implementation and success of the steam injection at LLNL in 1993 and at NAS Lemoore in 1994.  His research program has also produced advanced infrared wellbore temperature logging technologies and extraction well velocity, temperature, and concentration logging technology.
</h4>
<hr>
6147 Etcheverry Hall<br>
University of California<br>
Berkeley, CA, 94720<br>
Phone: (510) 642-2928<br>
FAX:   (510) 642-6163<br>
E-Mail: udell@euler.berkeley.edu
<hr>
<a href = "../../../BERC/Personnel/Udell/docs.html">List of Publications</a><br>
<a href = "CV.html">CV</a>
<hr>

