<head><title>Site 2</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 2</h1></center><hr>
<img src=../Pelican.gif align=right>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 2, the West Beach Landfill, occupies approximately 110 acres. The
initial construction of the landfill is done from 1956 to 1973. The full
disposal operations continued until 1978. Currently the site is not used for
air station operations or activities. Waste deposited included waste
chemical drums, municipal garbage, solvents, oily waste and sludges, paint
waste, plating wastes, industrial strippers and cleaners, acids, mercury,
polychlorinated biphenyl contaminated liquids, batteries, low-level
radiological waste, scrap metal, inert ordnance, asbestos, pesticides, tear
gas agent, infection medical waste, creosote, dredge spoils, and waste
medicines and reagents.<br clear=right>
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Semi-volatile organic compounds, aroclor 1260 & 1248, pesticides.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>Benzene, chlorobenzene, 1,2-dichloroethene, 1,1-dichloroethane, and
semi-volatile organic compounds.
<dt><b>Sediments from Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No samples collected.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
