<head><title>Site 3</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 3</h1></center><hr>
<img src=../Eastgate.gif align=right>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 3 is an abandoned fuel storage area which contained five storage tanks
for aviation gasoline, approximately 10,000 gallons each, which was
discovered to be leaking in 1975 and 1978. By 1987, all five tanks had been
drained, cleaned, and filled with water; all were later destroyed and buried
in place. The site is currently covered with grass and is used for an
aircraft exhibit.<br clear=right>
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Toluene, xylene, and petroleum hydrocarbons.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>Toluene and petroleum hydrocarbons.
<dt><b>Sediments from Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No samples collected.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
