<head><title>Site 4</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 4</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 4 consists of Building 360 which has been in operation since 1954. The
building houses machines shops, a paint shop, a parts cleaning shop, and a
plating shop. Processes performed in the plating shop included paint
stripping by blasting; chrome, silver, and nickel stripping; etching; and
chrome, silver, nickel, and copper plating.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>JP-5, motor oil, xylenes, ethylbenzene, toluene, trichloroethene,
1,1,1-trichloroethane, 1,1-dichloroethane, 1,1-dichloroethene, semi-volatile
organic compounds, cyanide, and chromium.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>Trichloroethene, 1,1-dichloroethene, 1,2-dichloroethene, and
1,1,1-trichloroethane.
<dt><b>Sediments from Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>Total petroleum hydrocarbons, chromium, cobalt, copper, lead,
molybdenum, nickel, and silver.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
