<head><title>Site 6</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 6</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 6 consists of Building 41 and was formerly used as a hangar for sea
planes and it was also used to store 55-gallon drums of waste from repair
and maintenance activities. These drums reportedly contained PD-680 dry
cleaner, trichlorofluoroethane, 6083 oil, 1,1,1-trichloroethane, paint waste
and strippers, and hydraulic fluids.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Semi-volatile organic compounds.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>1,1-dichloroethane, 1,2-dichloroethane, terachloroethene,
trichloroethene, and vinyl chloride.
<dt><b>Sediments from Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
