<head><title>Site 7A</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 7A</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 7A consists of Building 459 and has served as the NAS Alameda fuel
station since 1966. An auto repair shop and a small convenience store are
also part of the station facilities. Six 10,000-gallon underground storage
tanks were used to store gasoline and two abandoned 500-gallon tanks were
used to store solvents.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Ethylbenzene, toluene, xylenes, total petroleum
hydrocarbons, semi-volatile organic compounds, lead, and chromium.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>Benzene, ethylbenzene, toluene, xylenes, and total petroleum
hydrocarbons.
<dt><b>Sediments from Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
