<head><title>Site 7B</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 7B</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 7B consists of an area reportedly used by the Navy Exchange as a
service station. The area now is occupied by Building 162 and not used as a
service station. Building 162 is currently used as a maintenance shop for
ship components. Testing of small engines and pumps is conducted in
water-filled vats in the alleys surrounding Building 162.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>1,2-dichloroethene, xylenes, and semi-volatile compounds.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>Benzene, 1,2-dichloroethene, and vinyl chloride.
<dt><b>Sediments from Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
