<head><title>Site 7C</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 7C</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 7C is a former on-base annex service station not currently in
operation. The service station operated between 1971 and 1980. The site
includes three 12,000-gallon tanks and one of them was ruptured in 1980.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Benzene, ethylbenzene, toluene, xylenes, total petroleum hydrocarbons,
semi-volatile organic compounds, and lead.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>Benzene, ethylbenzene, toluene, xylenes, total petroleum hydrocarbons,
and semi-volatile organic compounds.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
