<head><title>Site 8</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 8</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 8 consists of Building 114. Building 114 was constructed in 1944 and
served as the Navy's Public Work Center maintenance and storage shop, office
equipment storage and appliance repair, and administrative office. The site
was also used as the center for weed and pest control on the base. PWC also
maintain other shops at Site 8. Activities at these shops included
woodworking, painting, and steam cleaning. An outside shed is
used for storing pesticides.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Semi-volatile organic compounds, polychlorinated biphenyl/pesticides,
and lead.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>Benzene, ethylbenzene, xylenes, and 1,2-dichloroethene.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>Motor oil, other total petroleum hydrocarbons, 1,2-dichloroethene, vinyl
chloride, PCB/pestcides, and semi-volatile organic compounds.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
