<head><title>Site 9</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 9</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 9 is approximately 1 acre in size and consists of Build 410 and the
area to the east of the building. Building 410 formerly housed the aircraft
paint stripping operation for NAS Alameda. Wastewater from the paint
stripping contained oil, paint, paint skins, detergent, and paint stripper.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Toluene and semi-volatile organic compounds.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>No chemicals of concern detected.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
