<head><title>Site 10A</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 10A</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 10A consists of Build 400 and the building was used from mid 1950's to
1972 for missile rework operations. From 1972 to the present, the building
has been used for paint stripping, constructing fiberglass aircraft
components, and aircraft parts cleaning operations. Prior io 1972, wastes
generated included paint sludges, metal shavings, paint strippers, cleaning
solvents, testing fluids, waste oil, and oil and grease. Wastes currently
generated at this site includes paint sludges, paint strippers, cleaning
solvents, waste oil, and oil and grease.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Semi-volatile organic compounds.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>1,1-dichloroethane, 1,2-dichloroethene, and trichloroethene.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>Lead, cadmium, and chromium.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
