<head><title>Site 10B</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 10B</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 10B is on the south side of Installation Restoration Site 13. The
building has been used for missile rework operation since 1972. Current
operations include electrical maintenance, cleaning, grinding, welding,
painting, paint stripping, and parts fabrication.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Toluene, ethylbenzene, xylenes, 2-methylnaphthalene,
di-n-butylphthalate, pyrene, total petroleum hydrocarbons.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd>Benzene, toluene, ethylbenzene, xylenes, naphthalene,
2-methylnaphthalene, total petroleum hydrocarbons.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
