<head><title>Site 11</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 11</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 11 consists of Building 14 and has been used for aircraft engine
testing since 1946. Fuel types used in testing include aviation gasoline,
JP-5 and JP-7.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Petroleum hydrocarbons, semi-volatile organic compounds, and lead.
<dt><b>Groundwater</b>
<dd>1,1-dichloroethane, 1,2-dichloroethene, trichloroethene, and vinyl
chloride.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
