<head><title>Site 12</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 12</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 12 consists of Building 10, the NAS Alameda power plant. Five
underground bunker "C" fuel oil storage tanks exists at this site and have
been closed and filled with sand. A six contained white gas was removed in
1993. Nine above ground tanks are used to store diesel fuel. Activities
conducted in the building include steam generation and air compression.
Historically, spills of diesel and petroleum products were documented.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Total petroleum hydrocarbons and semi-volatile organic compounds.
<dt><b>Groundwater</b>
<dd>1,2-dichloroethene, pyrene, phenanthrene, fluoranthene, acenaphthene.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>Total petroleum hydrocarbons, JP-5, semi-volatile organic compounds,
barium, chromium, copper, lead, nickel, zinc.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
