<head><title>Site 13</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 13</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 13 consists of approximately 30 acres and was formerly occupied by the
Pacific Coast Oil Works refinery, which operated between 1879 and 1903.
Refinery wastes and asphaltic residues were dumped at the site during the
period of operation. In 1991, a JP-5 release occurred on the east side of
Building 397.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Petroleum hydrocarbons, benzene, toluene, ethylbenzene, xylenes,
semi-volatile organic compounds, pesticides.
<dt><b>Groundwater</b>
<dd>Benzene, ethylbenzene, xylenes, 4,4-DDT, naphthalene,
2-methylnaphthalene.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
