<head><title>Site 14</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 14</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 14 was used until 1987 for fire training and fire extinguisher
discharging. The site consists of a steel tank installed on a concrete slab
that is surrounded on three sides by an earthen berm. Waste fuels from NAS
Alameda defueling operations were burned in the tank. Ansulite fire fighting
foam was mixed in a nearby tank and used to extinguish training fires.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Petroleum hydrocarbons, 4,4-DDT, 4,4-DDD, chlordane, endrin aldehyde,
PCB, dioxins, furans, semi-volatile organic compounds.
<dt><b>Groundwater</b>
<dd>1,2-dichloroethene.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
