<head><title>Site 15</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 15</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 15 consists of Building 301 and former Building 389. Building 301 was
used for storage of electrical equipment, oil-filled transformers, and oil,
unused machinery. Before Building 389 was torn down, it stored transformers.
Prior to 1974, transformers were stored on bare ground near these buildings.
An estimated 200 to 400 gallons of oil containing PCB from transformers may
have been stored at any one time. Currently, Building 301 is empty and the
remainder of the sites consists of an empty lot.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>PCB and lead.
<dt><b>Groundwater</b>
<dd>No significant chemicals of cencern.
<dt><b>Sediment in Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
