<head><title>Site 16</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 16</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 16 occupies 6.5 acres and is used as a storage yard.  It is located
between Eleventh and Twelvth Streets and north of N Avenue.  Large shipping
containters called CANS have been converted into storage containers.  Prior
to being a CANS storage area, the site had been used as a storage yard to
store paints, solvents, acids, bases, and transformers containing PCB oils.
PCBs were also sprayed on the ground for use in weed control.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Pesticides, PCBs, semi-volatile organic compounds, and toluene.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd> Trichloroethene.
<dt><b>Sediments from Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
