<head><title>Site 19</title></head>
<body background=../../../../BERC/UCSeal.gif>
<center><h1>Site 19</h1></center><hr>
<h2>Site History</h2><p>
Site 19 is located east of Ninth Street and north of K Street in an area
southwest of Building 360.  The Site has been used to store empty 55-gallon
drums and drums containing hazardous waste generated on the base.  It is
currently in use as a permitted storage area under RCRA for containerized
wastes generated by activities on NAS Alameda.
<hr>
<h2>Chemicals of Concern</h2><p>
<dl>
<dt><b>Soil</b>
<dd>Semi-volatile organic compounds, lead, total petroleum hydrocarbons,
toluene, xylenes,
ethylbenzene.
<dt><b>GroundWater</b>
<dd> Total petroleum hydrocarbons, 1,1-dichloroethane, 1,2-dichloroethene.
<dt><b>Sediments from Storm Sewer Drain</b>
<dd>No data available.
</dl>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
