<FONT SIZE=3 FACE="ARIAL" FONTCOLOR="#000000">The Southern California Biomedical Council (SCBC) is an industry association whose mission is to encourage networking and promote medical research and manufacturing in the Greater Los Angeles region. The Council is a non-profit, mutual-benefit California corporation. Membership is open to all for-profit and non-profit organizations engaged in medical technology development in southern California.<BR><BR>

SCBC recognizes that the needs of Greater LA's biomedical businesses are straightforward. Immediate access to sources of capital, information, customers, suppliers, and partners is key to success. The council created this web site for the purpose of encouraging virtual networking and maximizing access to resources essential for medical technology development. It takes advantage of the Internet's new connectivity paradigm to enable the region's firms to find and capitalize on new business opportunities worldwide to compete effectively.<BR><BR></FONT>

