</TD>

<TD width=400 Valign="texttop">
<FONT SIZE=3 face="arial" ><B>Since its founding in 1989, <B>MATECH</B> has become a recognized research laboratory in the development of optical, electronic, and biocompatible materials by chemical polymerization methods. Some of <B>MATECH</B>'s current research activities include optically-active glass-polymer nanocomposites for solid-state lasers and photochromics, microwave processing of materials, glass microsphere formation, flat-panel display technology, fiber-optics sensors, high temperature ceramic coatings for satellite positioning and apogee thrusters, and materials for artificial organs.<BR>
<BR>
Most recently, <B>MATECH</B> Biomedical Technologies has developed an encapsulation technology for the immunoisolation of living micro-organisms and live mammalian tissue cells, such as <I><B>E. coli</B></I>, <I><B>S. cerevisiae</B></I>, islets of Langerhans, hepatocytes, adrenal gland cells, for such diverse applications as biosensing, environmental remediation, pharmaceutical production, and transplantation of bioartificial organs for the potential treatment of diabetes, Parkinson's disease, liver disorders, and parathyroid deficiency.</B></FONT>

</TD></TR>

