<!-- Page Title: MATECH: About Founder -->
<!-- HTML Author: Ahmed A. Enany              -->
<!-- Graphics: Ahmed A. Enany                 -->
<!-- Copyright owner: MATECH                        -->
<!-- E-Mail: matech@sure.net                                 -->
<!-- **************************************** -->
<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>MATECH: About Founder</TITLE></HEAD><Meta name="description" content="MATECH was founded in 1989 by Dr. Edward J. A. Pope."></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#80FFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" ALINK="#FFFF00" VLINK="#FF00FF">

<BODY>
<CENTER><img src="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/logo6.jpg" Width=400 Height=78 Alt="logo"></CENTER>
<P>
<Center><img src="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/bar1.gif" Width=483 Heigtht 8 Alt="Bar"></Center>
<P>
<CENTER><H1><FONT SIZE=5><B>ABOUT FOUNDER</B></FONT></H1></CENTER><BR>
<img src="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/pope2.gif" Width=300 Height=270 Alt="Picture of Ed Pope" align=left>
Dr. Edward J. A Pope, President of MATECH Biomedical Technologies, received his BS (1983), MS (1995) and PhD (1989) degrees from the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA). He has published over 50 peer-reviewed technical papers in the field of material science and ceramics, received 4 patents, with several pending, and is co-editor of "Chemical Processing of Ceramics," published by Marcel-Dekker in 1994. Dr. Pope is also the lead-editor of "Sol-Gel Science and Technology," published by the American Ceramic Society in 1995. <BR><BR><BR>
<P>


Dr. Pope received the D. R. Ulrich Award for "outstanding work in the field of Sol-Gel Science & Technology" at the 8th International Workshop on Glasses and Ceramics from Gels in Faro, Portugal, September 18-22, 1955. He also received the Woldemar A. Weyl International Glass Science Award at the 17th International Congress on Glass, October 9-13, 1995, in Beijing, China.<BR>

<p>
<img src="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/pope1.gif" Width=300 Height=256 Alt="Picture of Ed Pope" align=right>
Dr. Pope served as the president of the UCLA Association of Chemists and Biochemists (1994-1995) and is a member of the UCLA Chemistry and Biochemistry Advisory Council, as well as the Executive Committee of the UCLA School of Engineering & Applied Science Dean's Council. He is a member of the UCLA Chancellor's Associates and a newly appointed member of the UCLA Government Relations Steering Committee, which promotes UCLA interests. Dr. Pope is a member of the Board of Directors of the Southern California Biomedical Council and a member of the steering committee of the Futurists Conference of Biomedical Innovations.<BR>

<p>

Dr. Pope is a member of the Central Committee of the California Republican Party (appointed by Assemblyman Nao Takasugi) and the Board of Directors of the Lincoln Club of Ventura County. He also serves on the Broad of Directors of the Rotary Club of Westlake Village.<BR>

<HR>
<FONT SIZE=3><CENTER>[<a href="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/index.htm">Home Page</a>][<a href="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/sensors.htm">Biosensors</a>][<a href="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/wellplat.htm">Fluorescent Reference Products</a>][<a href="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/diabetes.htm">Transplantation Therapy</a>]<BR>
