<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>MATECH: Company Focus</TITLE></HEAD><Meta name="description" content="MATECH is a research laboratory focusing on the development of optical, electronic, and biocompatible materials by chemical polymerization methods for biosensing, environmental and pharmaceutical applications.">
<Body background="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/chem1.gif" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" ALINK="#FFFF00" VLINK="#FF00FF">

<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=600>

<TR><TD Width=151>
<CENTER><img src="http://www.socalbio.org/matech/lab.gif" Width=151 Height=91 Alt="Picture of Matech's Facility"></CENTER><BR>
<FONT SIZE=2><CENTER>31304 Via Colinas, Ste. 102, <BR>
Westlake Village, CA 91362<BR>
USA</CENTER></FONT>

<CENTER>
<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<td bgcolor="#FFFF80">
E-mail: <a href="mailto:matech@sure.net">matech@sure.net</a>
</td>
</table></CENTER>

</TD>

<TD Width=444 height=184>
<img src="wlcome.gif" Width=193 Height=35 Alt="Welcome">
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><img src="mast.gif" width=394 height=86 alt="mast"></CENTER></td>


</Table></CENTER></TR>

<BR>
<BR>

<TABLE width=600 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3>
<TR><TD width=200 bgcolor="#FFFF80" Valign="texttop">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5 FACE="SCRIPT"><B>MENU</B></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<CENTER><FORM METHOD="LINK" ACTION="guest.htm">
<INPUT TYPE="SUBMIT" VALUE="Sign Guestbook">
</FORM></CENTER>
<img src="ball3.gif" align=middle><a href="wellplat.htm"><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="ARIAL"> Fluorescent Reference Plate</FONT></a><BR><BR>
<img src="ball3.gif" align=middle><a href="sensors.htm"><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="ARIAL"> Biosensors</FONT></a><BR><BR>
<img src="ball3.gif" align=middle><a href="diabetes.htm"><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="ARIAL">Transplantation Therapy</FONT></a><BR><BR>
<img src="ball3.gif" align=middle><a href="biolink.htm"><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="ARIAL"> Links to Biomaterials Sites</FONT></a><BR><BR>
<img src="ball3.gif" align=middle><a href="pope.htm"><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="ARIAL">About Founder</FONT></a><BR><BR>
<img src="ball3.gif" align=middle><a href="press.htm"><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="ARIAL"> Press Releases</FONT></a><BR><BR>
<img src="ball3.gif" align=middle><a href="mailto:matech@sure.net"><FONT SIZE=2><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="ARIAL">Contact MATECH</FONT></a><BR><BR>
<img src="ball3.gif" align=middle><a href="http://www.socalbio.org/menu.htm"><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="ARIAL"> Go to SCBC's Main Menu</FONT></a>

</TD>

<TD width=400 Valign="texttop">
<FONT SIZE=3 face="arial" ><B>Since its founding in 1989, <B>MATECH</B> has become a recognized research laboratory in the development of optical, electronic, and biocompatible materials by chemical polymerization methods. Some of <B>MATECH</B>'s current research activities include optically-active glass-polymer nanocomposites for solid-state lasers and photochromics, microwave processing of materials, glass microsphere formation, flat-panel display technology, fiber-optics sensors, high temperature ceramic coatings for satellite positioning and apogee thrusters, and materials for artificial organs.<BR>
<BR>
Most recently, <B>MATECH</B> Biomedical Technologies has developed an encapsulation technology for the immunoisolation of living micro-organisms and live mammalian tissue cells, such as <I><B>E. coli</B></I>, <I><B>S. cerevisiae</B></I>, islets of Langerhans, hepatocytes, adrenal gland cells, for such diverse applications as biosensing, environmental remediation, pharmaceutical production, and transplantation of bioartificial organs for the potential treatment of diabetes, Parkinson's disease, liver disorders, and parathyroid deficiency.</B></FONT>

</TD></TR>

</TABLE>

