<!-- Page Title: SCBC: Workshop on Design Controls-->
<!-- HTML Author: Ahmed A. Enany              -->
<!-- Graphics: Ahmed A. Enany                 -->
<!-- Copyright owner: SCBC                    -->
<!-- E-Mail: scbc@socalbio.org                -->
<!-- **************************************** -->
<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>YOU ARE INVITED TO THE SIXTH BIOMEDICAL INDUSTRY BREAKFAST 
</TITLE></HEAD>
<body background="http://www.socalbio.org/graph/bk1.gif">
<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=5 FACE="ARIAL">COME TO THE SCBC SIXTH BIOMEDICAL INDUSTRY BREAKFAST 
</FONT></B></CENTER>

<HR>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="reg.htm"><FONT SIZE =5><B><I>Click Here To Register On-line.</I></B></FONT></A></address><BR>
<IMG SRC="http://www.socalbio.org/graph/IPHNMAN.GIF" ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE =5>Or call 213-236-4890 to register by phone.</FONT><BR><BR><BR>
<HR>

<FONT SIZE =4 face="arial"><UL><LI>Date: December 16 (Monday), 1996 
<LI>Time: From 8:00 a.m. to 11:00 p.m. 
<LI>Place: Sportsmen's Lodge (Regency Room) at the corner of 
Ventura Blvd. and Coldwater Canyon
<LI>Address: 12833 Ventura Blvd. (Studio City in the San Fernando Valley)
<LI>Fee: $30 for the SCBC members and $50 for non-members  
(inc. breakfast and printed materials) 
 </UL>

</FONT>
<HR>

<FONT SIZE=4 FACE="ARIAL">There is no doubt that biomedical technology is one of the important components of 
Southern California's new economy. A recent article by James Flanigan of the LA Times 
(Nov. 13, 1996, Business Section) even proclaims that this industry could be a salve for 
the region's economy which is still trying to make up for the loss of aerospace jobs. 
This however is not going to happen without, among other things, an enlightened and 
activist public policy based on your input to remove some of the obstacles facing 
biomedical and biotechnology entrepreneurs in the region and to provide the needed 
business incentives to retain and grow Greater LA's biomedical firms. This is the focus of 
the SCBC 6th Biomedical Industry Breakfast. </FONT><BR><BR>
 
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="ARIAL"><B>Come and share your thoughts and concerns about the future of Greater LA's biomedical and biotechnology businesses with our distinguished guests:</B> </FONT></CENTER><BR><BR>
 
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5 FACE="ARIAL"><B>Linda Griego</B> </FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=4 FACE="ARIAL"><I>(President and CEO, Rebuild LA)</I></FONT></CENTER><BR><BR>
 
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5 FACE="ARIAL"><B>Congressman Howard Berman</B> </FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=4 FACE="ARIAL"><I>(D- 26th Congressional District which includes <BR>
Van Nuys, Sylmar, Pacoima, San Fernando,  <BR>
Sun Valley and North Hollywood) </I></FONT></CENTER><BR><BR>
 
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5 FACE="ARIAL"><B>Gary Mendoza</B></FONT> <BR>
<FONT SIZE=4 FACE="ARIAL"><I>(Deputy Mayor for Economic Development, <BR>
City of Los Angeles) <BR></I></FONT></CENTER>
 
 
<HR>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="reg.htm"><FONT SIZE =5><B><I>Click Here To Register On-line.</I></B></FONT></A></address><BR>
<IMG SRC="http://www.socalbio.org/graph/IPHNMAN.GIF" ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE =5>Or call 213-236-4890 to register by phone.</FONT><BR>
<P>
