<CENTER><H2>SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA BIOMEDICAL COUNCIL</H2></CENTER>
<B><CENTER><H3>LINKS TO SOURCES OF FINANCE AND VENTURE CAPITAL</CENTER></H3></B>

<HR>
<CENTER><FORM METHOD="LINK" ACTION="http://www.socalbio.org/registry.htm">
<INPUT TYPE="SUBMIT" VALUE="Add a Link"></CENTER></FORM>
<HR>

<UL>
<li><a href="http://www.accel.com/">Accel Partners</a> - a venture capital firm focusing on information and health care technologies.

<li><a href="http://www.erols.com/aciipo/index.html">A.C.I.</a>  - helps in IPO and handles securities consulting and investor relations

<li><a href="http://www.databack.com/~adsfin/">ADS Financial</a> - provides expansion stage capital, strategic alliance capital and LBO financing.


<li><A HREF="http://www.acm.com/acm/">Adams Capital Management</A> - invests in information technology, health care and manufacturing companies.

<li><a href="http://www.atv.com/~fleming/">Alliance Technology Ventures</a> - provides early-stage venture capital for life sciences and information technology start ups.

<li><a href="http://www.businessexchange.com/">American Venture Capital Exchange</a> - This site lists new ventures seeking capital and companies available for acquisition.

<li><a href="http://biospace.com/exhib_script/exhibs/Asset_Management_Company.html"> Asset Management</a> - Start-up companies in the physical, computer and biological sciences. $1M min.

<li><A HREF="http://www.avicapital.com/">Associated  Venture Investors</A> - seed and early stage venture capital since 1982.

<li><a href="http://www.atlasventure.com">Atlas Venture</a> - an international venture capital firm that finances high technology ventures.

<li><a href="http://www.austinventures.com/austinventures/index.html">Austin Ventures</a> - raises private equity capital for growth companies in the Southwest.

<li><a href="http://www.avicapital.com/">AVI Capital, L.P.</a> - a venture capital partnership specializing in seed and early-stage investments in high-technology companies.


<li><a href="http://execpc.com/~bcmbio">Benchmark Capital Management</a> - Investment advisory firm specializing in biotechnology investment management for individual and institutional investors.

<li><a href="http://www.cris.com/~1capital/INDEX.HTM">Berkshire Capital Group</a> - provides financial services to  emerging growth industries having specific money needs.

<li><A HREF="http://www.bedco.com">Burr, Egan, Deleage & Co.</A> - is a private venture capital firm  with investments in over 200 companies throughout the US. Focus:  Information Technology, Life Sciences, and Communications.

<li><a href="http://www.zdh.com/~njiw/cmc.html">C.M.C. Group Financiers</a> - commercial loans and  venture capital.

<li><a href="http://www-dev.cecase.ukans.edu/cambell-becker/html/cbi-home.html">Campbell-Becker, Inc.</a> - is in the business of managing venture capital funds focusing on start-up and early stage, advanced technology companies.

<li><a href="http://www.inch.com/~capital/cap.html">Capital Access Partners</a> - an investment group specializing in the telecom., electronics, and medical device industries.

<li><a href="http://www.dnai.com/~jlebeau/cpv/">Capital Partnership</a>

<li><a href="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/Ken_Giffin/">Capital Quest</a> - assists businesses in acquiring venture capital. 

<li><a href="http://www.cgcfin.com/">Concord Growth Corporation</a> - financing and cash flow management products for small business needs.

<li><a href="http://www.Iplex.com/cyberspace">Cyberspace Services</a> - financing assistance for technology businesses.

<li><a href="http://www.tcd.net/~dcm/">DCM Finance</a> - provides finance for start-ups.

<li><a href="http://www.descovc.com/">Desco Venture Capital Group</a> - funds for start-ups and emerging technology companies.  

<li><a href="http://www.biospace.com/g/synd/exhib_script/exhibitors/DomainAssociates.html">Domain Associates</a> supports technology-based companies focused on life sciences, including biopharmaceuticals, medical devices, bio-instrumentation, diagnostics, and new materials as applied to health care.

<li><a href="http://www.drapervc.com/">Draper Fisher Associates</a> - a venture capital firm having investments in numerous high-tech companies.

<li><a href="http://www.dynastycap.com/">Dynasty Capital Services Consulting</a> - consults with emerging technology companies from  startup to IPO and beyond.

<li><A HREF="http://www.smokedsalmon.com/enercana/general.html">Enercana Capital Ltd.</a> - is a Canadian venture capital company.

<li><a href="http://www.entreeltd.com/">Entree Ltd.</a>

<li><a href="http://www.tig.com/Fostin/index.html">Fostin Capital Partners</a> - invests in privately-held entrepreneurial companies.

<li><a href="http://www.scsn.net/~jonredd/">Gold-Hammer Venture Development</a> - venture development for start-ups and expansions.

<li><a href="http://www.humwin.com">Hummer Winblad Venture Partners</a> - the first venture capital fund exclusively focused on investing in software companies.

<li><a href="http://www.netsmart.com/ivp/">Institutional Venture Partners (IVP)</a> - a privately held, professionally managed family of venture capital partnerships.

<li><a href="http://apollo.co.uk/a/International_Funding/">International Funding</a> - provides commercial loans and venture capital.

<li><a href="http://www.income.com/inv.htm">InvNet</a>  - provides funds from $5,000 to $250,000,000. Canadian/US and international placements.

<LI>Johnnie D. Johnson  Co., Inc. - Investor Relations and Corporate PR services for publicly traded corporations.  Expertise in
health-care corporations.  New York based international firm. Address: 333 S. Grand, #3590, LA, CA 90071. Contact Person: James Lucas. Phone: 213-626-4848. Fax: 213-626-1303. E-mail Address: 73531.1041@compuserve.com.

<li><A HREF="http://www.jjdc.com/">Johnson & Johnson Development Corporation</A> - supports new technology in the health care industry.

<li><a href="http://www.kcapital.com/">Kirkland Capital</a> - provides seed capital to software entrepreneurs.

<li><a href="http://www.home.net/home2/kpcb/kpcb.html">Kleiner Perkins Caufield &amp; Byers</a> - venture capital firm in investing in high-tech companies.

<li><a href="http://www.gate.net/~wun4all/">LifeWorks! Entrepreneurial Site</a> - arranges business loans, hard money, venture capital, real estate, and factoring.

<li>
<a href="http://www.lwt.com/">LWT Capital Management</a> - venture capital for early-stage companies in the information technology and communications industries. 

<li><a href="http://www.mandi.com/index.html">Mehta and Isaly Worldwide Health care Investments</a> - institutional investors focusing on pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies worldwide.  

<li><a href="http://www.norwestvc.com/">Norwest Venture Capital</a> - venture capital firm based in Minneapolis, MN with offices in Boston, MA and Menlo Park, CA.

<li><a href="http://www.nvst.com/">NVST</a> - venture capital investment network. 

<li><a href="http://www.htm.net/gilbert">O.R. Gilbert Enterprises</a> - capital resource specialist representing national funding companies which provide fast and efficient cash from account receivables.

<li><a href="http://www.oakinv.com/">Oak Investment Partners</a> - focuses on information technology, biotechnology and retail market sectors.

<li><a href="http://product.com/olympic/">Olympic Venture Partners</a> - provides venture capital financing to early-stage technology companies in the western third of North America.

<li><a href="http://www.opuscapital.com/">Opus Capital</a> - provides access to capital and operational expertise.  

<li><a href="http://biospace.com/exhib_script/exhibs/Oxford_Bioscience_Partners.html"> Oxford Bioscience Partners </a> - focuses on health care and bioscience opportunities. Seed, start-up and later stage investing.

<li><a href="http://www.ptvchina.com/">Pacific Technology Venture Fund-China</a>

<li><a href="http://www.muskoka.com/pegasus/">Pegasus Group International Ltd</a> - venture capital. 

<li><a href="http://www.partechsf.com/">Partech International</a> - a venture capital firm investing in start ups and growth  companies in information, communications, and  health care technologies.  

<li><a href="http://allcities.org/pauley/index.html">Pauley Financial</a> - focuses on environmental and high tech companies

<li><a href="http://www.pioneer-capital.com/">Pioneer Capital Corporation</a>  - early stage and growth venture capital for New  England-based businesses.

<li><a href="http://www.dvbiznet.com/PLEXUS/">Plexus Ventures, Inc</a> - investment capital and  corporate development advice, consulting and services to  pharmaceutical, biotechnology and drug delivery  companies.  

<li><a href="http://www.thevine.com/pcap/">Princeton Capital Finance Company</a> - provides asset-based lending.

<li><a href="http://www.quaestus.com/">Quaestus Management Corporation</a> - invests exclusively in information services and  technology companies.  

<li><a href="http://www.dirs.com/vc/rji/">RJI International Consulting Financing Inc.</a> - locates venture capital for start ups. 

<li><a href="http://iplex.com/rls">RLS, Inc.</a> - Venture Capital consulting.

<li><a href="http://www-personal.usfca.edu/~alvaal00/sfve.html">San Francisco Venture Enterprises</a>

<li><a href="http://www.sierraven.com/">Sierra Ventures</a> - provides financing to start-up and emerging growth companies in information technology and health care.

<li><A HREF="http://www.winternet.com/~kcarney/">St. Paul Venture Capital</A> - provides entrepreneurs with the experience, resources and capital required to build successful businesses from promising ideas.

<li><a href="http://www.t8000.com/scorp/scorp.htm">Swancorp Equities Inc.</a> - provides corporate finance and Investor Relations services to public and private companies.

<li><a href="http://www.ibb.com/tke.html">TKE Capital Investments Inc</a>

<li><a href="http://www.tridentcap.com/">Trident Capital, L. P</a>

<li><a href="http://www.vencom.com/wmi/vc">VenCom</a> - invests in technology and communications-related ventures and start-ups.

<li><a href="http://www.venrock.com/">Venrock Associates</a> - invests in information  sciences, health care and biotechnology.  

<li><a href="http://www.linex.com/venres/">Venture Resources</a> - focuses on health care, biomedical, early stage technically based companies and ventures.

<li><a href="http://www.vistaweb.com/vista">Vista Venture Capital</a> - equity capital  for cutting-edge technologies. 

<li><a href="http://www.caprel.com/xtv/xtv.html">Xerox Technology Ventures</a> - An independently managed venture capital group operating under the aegis of Xerox Corporation.</UL>
